EASY SPICY TUNA POKE BOWLS🐟🥣🌶️ (full recipe below)

I think spicy tuna bowls are the new hot girl meal. I know raw fish can be a little intimidating, so make sure you buy previously flash-frozen fish from a grocer that you trust! I buy my ahi tuna filets from @Sprouts and eat them the day of.

✨Ingredients (4 servings) // about 60gr protein per portion 

-1 1/2 lbs raw ahi tuna (2 steaks)
-1 1/2 tbsp sriracha
-2-3 tbsp aminos or soy sauce
-3 tbsp Kewpie mayonnaise
-1 cup edamame
-1 hass avocado
-1 cup uncooked sushi rice
-1 tbsp mirin
-1 tbsp rice vinegar
-1/2 tbsp sesame oil
-1 tsp salt
-1 tsp sesame seeds

Pat dry ahi tuna and cut it into 1-inch cubes. Place inside a bowl and add sriracha, aminos, and mayo. Stir until combined, cover, and rest refrigerated for at least 15 minutes. Cook sushi rice according to the instructions on the package. Warm up frozen edamame by pouring boiling water on top and letting it sit for 5 minutes. Slice avocado or mash it; feel free to season it however you like. Add mirin, rice vinegar, sesame oil, and salt to cooked rice. Stir and use it as a base for your bowl. Continue plating by adding about 4 ounces of tuna, 1/4 cup of edamame, and 1/4-1/2 an avocado. Portions are up to you! Top with sesame seeds, and feel free to add any extra sauce and seasonings like furikake. Enjoy immediately and save any leftovers in a tight-lid container in the fridge. Eat the same day.

I surprised Rell with pictures of her baby sister! She was so excited & in love! 🥰 her big proud smile, the kiss for baby, & even putting her feet up by her head like baby melted me. 🥹 she’s going to be a great big sister! 🙏

Baby names… bring them on!!! 🤍 We’re pretty sure we have a name, but we’re waiting until we meet her to officially name her! 
—
We had a different name for Rell most of my pregnancy with her, but the last week of my pregnancy Taylor shared the name Rell (and Rell Sunn’s story) with me— and the moment we met her, the other name disappeared- she was 💯 Rell! So needless to say, backups are welcome!! 🙏🙏

The other day was my day for the “dreaded Glucose test” that typically happens between week 24-28 of pregnancy. I went an alternative route during my pregnancy with Rell so I never experienced the glucola drink, BUT this time my doctor offered a natural alternative to the standard glucose drink, called the Fresh Test. (I have no affiliation with this) It ended up not being so “dreaded” of an experience after all.
It still creates that glucose load with 50g of sugar, but it tastes like a refreshing lemonade and it’s non-gmo, with no additives and preservatives, and I didn’t feel icky at all. (It does warn that some may experience side effects— that is a lot of sugar at once!) I was even able to eat a boiled egg before my test as mine was a non-fasting test, but of course follow what your provider suggests! I mixed the powder with some water and drank it an hour before my blood draw. The visit to the lab was easy. And now I just wait for my results! 🙏🙏
__
I wanted to share this quick experience and just bring awareness that there is a natural alternative that you can explore with your doctor when it’s time for your Glucose Test during pregnancy. Obviously this is an important step for mama and baby during pregnancy, so this is up to you and your doctor, but I personally love learning about other alternatives that feel right to me.

SAVE this for a quick Egg Free Breakfast option!
Rell has never liked eggs- never. Which led us to exploring if there was something instinctual behind it and we learned she had an egg allergy when she was a baby. The great news is, she can eat eggs baked into things, and I think she’s growing out of this allergy BUT she still dislikes eggs. Obviously eggs are an easy and awesome way for quick protein for breakfast— especially in the form of egg bites! SO it was time to explore a new Quick Protein option for breakfast and she LOVES these Sausage bites! We call them “muffins” 😉 Wether you’re catering to an egg allergy in your home or not- this is a great breakfast alternative to keep in your fridge or freezer for when you need a quick and healthy breakfast grab!
*I make these gluten free- and they can easily be made dairy free!
—
RECIPE
-1lb ground Breakfast Sausage
-1-2 cups finely chopped broccoli florets (optional, but a great way to add greens into breakfast!)
-1 cup your choice of gluten free flour (I used Bob’s Red Mill Paleo All Purpose mix)
-1 tsp baking powder
-1 cup shredded cheese- I use goat cheddar. You can simply make this dairy free with a dairy free cheese alternative!
-3/4 cup Almond Milk (or your choice of milk)
—
•Sauté 1 lb breakfast sausage & finely chopped broccoli florets in avocado oil until sausage is fully cooked 
•In a mixing bowl, add 1 cup gluten free flour, 
1 tsp baking powder, & mix together. 
•Then add 1 cup shredded cheese. Mix all together.
•Add and mix in cooked sausage & broccoli to the dry mix. 
•Add 3/4 cup of Almond Milk. Mix together well.
•Scoop mixture into pre-greased cupcake pan- I use avocado oil spray. 
•Bake for 20-25 minutes at 400 degrees.

Enjoy these!! You can store in the fridge for a few days, or freeze them for when needed! Approved by my toddler— and my husband and I love them too!

#eggfreebreakfast #glutenfree #toddlerbreakfast #glutenfreebreakfast

A MUST on your weekly meal rotation! SAVE for this delicious Sausage, Kale, Ravioli soup. This was inspired by another recipe I saw via Instagram, but I made some upgrades to make it Gluten Free and healthier! We use a Grain Free Ravioli- but you can use a gluten free ravioli/tortellini, or any type of Gluten Free Pasta! I suggest a simple pasta if you’re wanting to make this Dairy Free.
Oh, and obviously, wait til it’s cooled down to eat— I basically burned my mouth in the making of this reel!😂
__
Ingredients
-1 lb Spicy or Mild Italian chicken Sausage— I buy this from the meat counter at the grocery store. 
-1 small yellow onion, diced
-5-7 cloves garlic, minced
-3 Tbsp Gluten Free flour (I use Bob’s Red Mill Paleo all purpose flour mix)
-1 tsp dried basil
-½ tsp dried oregano
-a pinch of cayenne (omit if you’re trying to keep the spice level low)
-1 tsp (gluten free) hot sauce (I use Sweet Baby Ray’s hot sauce- equivalent to Franks)
-½ tspmustard powder
-1 cup full fat Coconut Milk (I prefer it canned)
-32 oz Chicken Broth (I used Kettle & Fire)
-2-3 cups organic kale, chopped
-1 Box of @cappellos Grain Free Ravioli (I find this in the freezer section, and try to thaw for a bit before cooking) OR use your choice of gfree pasta or gluten free tortellini!
-Pink Salt and Pepper to taste. 
-optional: pinch red pepper chili flakes
Instructions
-Spray Large pot with Avocado Oil, and cook the sausage (remove the casing if using sausage links) and diced onions, and garlic over medium-high heat until the onions and garlic are softened and the sausage is cooked through.  -Add your gluten free flour and cook for about 2 minutes, to cook the flour in.
-Add basil, oregano, cayenne, hot sauce, and mustard powder. Stir to combine. -Add the chicken broth, add and stir in Coconut Milk. While stirring, “clean” the bottom of the pot.
-Bring to a boil, (if using regular gluten free pasta, add it in now to cook while it’s boiling) Reduce to a simmer. -Add ravioli to cook about 5-8 minutes, depending on its cooking time. Bring to a simmer.
-Add the Kale, and stir it into cook. -Add in red chili flakes, pink salt, pepper to taste!
ENJOY!! ❤️

😞 This is difficult for me to write. Last week I stepped outside my comfort zone and shared a very personal goal of mine to have my book make the New York Times Best Seller list. 😱 The list isn’t released until this Sunday but my editor at NatGeo said publishers find out a few days early and she would call me right away. I got the call. She shared the sad news that I didn’t make the list. 😔 I kept it together on the call..but the tears came hard as soon as we said bye. I’m surprised I care so much about this. I cried for about 5 minutes and after a great pep talk from a supportive husband was able to pick myself up. 🥹

💛 I want to make it clear that above all, I’m extremely proud of my book and don’t want this to cast any sort of shadow over the past 4 years that were nothing but a positive experience of writing and creating this treasure for families all around the world. 🌎 The quality of my hard work is definitely more important than the accolade of New York Times Best Seller. But I think, if I were to try my best to explain why I’m feeling so sad and even slightly embarrassed it’s because 2 things: I’ve never wanted anything like this for myself. I’m sure so many other mothers out there can relate. I endlessly cheer and support my family, but rarely do I want something so purely for myself. This was that for me. ❤️

Secondly, the Bucket List community has rallied so hard behind me. I have have felt it every day of this journey. I was excited to celebrate this achievement all of us together. ❤️💙💚 You’ve done so much for me. Thx to you, we’ve surpassed NatGeo’s presale records. I’m going to keep my head up and focus on the positive. There’s still chance I may make the list in future weeks so I’ll keep trying my best. Positive reviews of my book on Amazon and Goodreads help so much. ⭐️ I want you to know that I screenshot your thoughtful reviews and every time you share my book on Instagram in such cute creative ways and add it to a journal I’ve been keeping of this book publishing journey. Thank you for being a part of my story and all the ups and downs. This day is a down for me. But I know I can get back up..❤️ Jess

Commencing with eager anticipation, the fourth day of Chhath Puja, termed “Usha Arghya,” sees devotees awakening at dawn to perform rituals by water bodies. Clad in traditional attire, they engage in a profound expression of gratitude to the rising sun, standing in water and offering obeisance. The day encapsulates themes of spiritual purification and the renewal of life-sustaining energy drawn from the sun god. As the sun ascends, meticulous cleaning of worship spaces precedes the heartfelt ceremonies. The conclusion is marked by communal gatherings for joyous feasts, solidifying the sense of community and reverence for the celestial deity. 😍🙏 #therawtextures #bigindianwanderers #chhathpuja #chhathmahaparv #bihari #chhath #bihar

“Furniture… lots of furniture!” @klekktic 

The Matrix is one of my all time favourite movies. It came out 25 years ago, inspiring a whole generation of filmmakers, visual effects artists and stunt coordinators. 

This is my take on the iconic “guns, lots of guns” scene where Neo & Trinity enter The Matrix to prepare for battle. I thought this would be a fun and innovative way of showcasing a furniture brand. Having different products from the @klekktic collection flying into the Matrix. 

To execute this @shravanraoo & I shot for a full 12 hours in a studio in Dubai. Heba, the founder of Klekktic, who plays Trinity in this video, helped coordinate all of the Klekktic pieces to be shipped to the studio. We then placed each item one by one filming the product and then removing it. This allowed us to create the effect of different pieces flying into place.

@Klekktic is a beautiful UAE based brand. They have a minimal design aesthetic that is clean and elegant. The best part about their products is they are customizable. For example, the desk at the start of the video I fully customized from a dining room table into an office desk with draws and storage. Bed sizes, table lengths, mirror finishings etc can all be customized to fit your space size and preference. 

My home project is really starting to take shape. It’s been a long time coming but it’s been worth the wait. More coming on that soon…

Special shout out to @shravanraoo who helped me film this and then worked on the kick ass visual effects. 

What do you guys think of the video? Drop a Matrix reference comment below if you liked the video!

What do you know about Venezuela? 🇻🇪 

Back in July I had the opportunity to spend a few weeks in Venezuela creating something special for @beautifuldestinations. 

As 2023 has been the year of AI, I’ve been wanting to innovate and figure out a way to combine new immersive AI visuals with travel content. My thinking was that we’d be going to a place that not many people have seen before, Angel Falls in Canaima National Park, and if we could combine never before seen AI content with a truly out of this world destination then we’d have all the ingredients for something special. 

The first person I called was @andras.ra who’s been diving into short form AI content this year. We’ve worked together a ton over the years and he’s an editing magician. The idea developed into a FPV Drone only concept where we’d play with generative AI to add little details into the video. @reme_martyr then joined the team to execute the aerials, he killed it! As the concept got bigger so did the team with @alexislefrene , @shravanraoo , @andres.visual and @bahaamalaeb joining the squad. 

What started as a fun idea turned into a full blown innovation project, looking to create the world’s first AI supported Tourism Campaign. By tapping into unique visual styles the hope was to create something that would make some noise and spark a conversation about the destination.

What you wouldn’t know is that 40 years ago my parents lived in Venezuela. At that time, Caracas was a global advertising hub. Ironically, my Dad was working in the same field that I am now. Back then he was one of the few photographers paving the way through dark room visual effects, that’s before photoshop existed! It was very cool to be there 40 years later trying to do something similar, as Venezuela announces itself as a new and exciting Tourism destination. I love the country’s new branding “open to the future” and I hope this video gives you a glimpse of that future as well as the future of content and where I think it’s going. 

This video is quite the rollercoaster so fasten your seat belt and enjoy the ride…

Special thanks to @vidafuria & @campamentouruyen 

#Venezuela #canaima #angelfalls

Back to the future with @tomjauncey 

Imagine time traveling from 1971 to 2071. That’s the idea behind this iPhone only video for @visit.dubai 

“I wanted to create something fun in Dubai that would throw us back to the 70s. It’s a period of time that is so influential in today’s mainstream music and fashion worlds. To create that authentic feel I teamed up with Dubai based fashion designer @dianamuza_ to customize a handmade 70s outfit with all the materials and accessories coming from Deira. For the music I worked with internationally renowned DJ & Producer, @guest_cuts , to digitally remaster a vinyl track from the 70s to give the video that feel good disco vibe.

I love coming up with original ideas and doing things a little different. As the UAE was founded in 1971 I thought it would be fun to take a trip to the future! The challenge was to create something unique, shot only on iPhone, that would juxtapose a retro vibe with a futuristic setting. There’s no better location in Dubai for a time machine than the Museum of the Future. 

Special thanks to @omararef , @krimium , @bramhansel , @basso2012 , @nickeeyy and @museumofthefuture for the onground support, filming and editing.

Puppies & Pilates 🐕🦾

For the last month I’ve been doing Pilates with the awesome Gaby Noble founder of @exhalepilateslondon, as a way to improve my strength training. Prior to this year I had no idea what Pilates was and always thought of it as a workout for women. I couldn’t have been more wrong. 

As I wait for Project Apartment to get fully underway I’ve turned my empty home into a Pilates Studio. This is just one of the many brutal exercises that are getting me lifting heavier than I ever have and feeling more recovered each day. 

There’s a big reason why a lot of elite male athletes, celebrities and performers have added Pilates to their training regimes 👇🏽

- Improves your muscle to mind connection. I am so focused on the movements and getting the muscles to do exactly what it needs to do. Something I never think about when weightlifting. 

- Improves core strength. Killer ab workout every single time!

- Helps me lift more, squat deeper, recover quicker, lets the joints and muscles breathe. This is why it’s been the perfect supplement to my strength training. 

- Limits injuries so I can keep pushing towards my goals without set backs. My flexibility and mobility has completely changed in 1 month. Again, allowing me to lift heavier, get stronger and recover faster. 

- Improves your posture & helps keep a healthy spine. Both are key for the work I do and ultimately make me move better and with more ease.

This is just the start of my Pilates journey but I’ve been loving it so far with Gaby Noble @exhalepilateslondon . If you’re interested in trying it out shoot her a message. She’s the best in the space and trained the likes of Harry Styles, Kate Moss, Giancarlo Esposito & Christian Eriksen. 

How many of you guys have done Pilates?

My new morning routine… 🏊🏽‍♂️🔥 @osn 

Here’s another Dragon encounter that you may not have seen yet. Last year I was very fortunate to work on the launch of HBO’s Game of Thrones prequel, House of the Dragon, streaming on OSN+. It was hands down one of the best experiences of my career, working on something that really pushed the boundaries from a marketing standpoint. 

I came up with a simple concept, “what if Dragons actually lived in today’s world and how would we interact with them?”

This video was shot at the iconic @habitasalula property in Saudi Arabia. Visuals from this pool were starting to blow up online as a bucket list hot spot due to its unique positioning in the desert, amongst a ton of crazy rock formations. We felt it was the perfect place for some Dragons to be lurking around 👀.

Huge thank you to the team @osn for trusting in the vision, to @filmalula & @experiencealula for their on the ground support, @habitasalula for allowing us to execute this idea, @itsprestonchen for shooting it with me and the awesome @krimium for the wow factor VFX edit.

$5 gets you this Dubai Fountain view 🔥 

TRAVEL TIP - For anyone visiting Dubai who wants a killer photo or video, definitely visit The Dubai Fountain Boardwalk. A ticket costs you 15 AED which is less than $5. For that you can get up close and personal with the Fountains. Shows run daily from 5:45pm to 11:30pm. This ticket allows for multiple entries too so you can ensure you get the shot you wanted. 

I had no idea about this experience and thought it was super cool. Let me know if you want me to share more of these kind of tips or information 😉.

WERBUNG: Ich bin einfach nur stolz Leute! Ich bin ab sofort der Brand Ambassador von @fortiswatches und darf eine echte Schweizer Toolwatch an meinem Handgelenk tragen! Und das Krasse ist: Ihr könnt am Ende des Jahres meine Fortis Novonaut gewinnen! Ein echter Hammer, denn die Uhr hat einen Wert von ca 5.000€. Fortis hat eine über 100-jährige Tradition, sie haben die erste automatische Armbanduhr der Welt (!!!) gebaut, sind Weltraumgetestet und ein mega sympathisches Familienunternehmen das brauchbaren Luxus baut! 
Meine ganz persönliche Geschichte mit Fortis: Meine allererste Automatikuhr war tatsächlich eine Fortis Flieger. Hab ich im Jahr 2000 von nem sehr guten Freund von mir gebraucht gekauft. Grüße gehen raus an Norbert🤝. Also die gemeinsame Geschichte Fortis  x Malmedie steht definitiv.
 
Was müsst Ihr machen, um die Novonaut zu gewinnen?
1. @fortiswatches folgen
2. @matthiasmalmedie folgen
3. Fotos & Reels @fortiswatches liken, gerne kommentieren und mit Euren Freunden teilen
4. An meinem Geburtstag 03.12.2024 postet @fortiswatches das Gewinnspiel final. Liken und vor allem kommentieren, warum gerade Ihr die Novonaut bekommen solltet.  Am 10.12.2024 benachrichtigen wir die/den GewinnerIn, sodass die oder derjenige seine neue Fortis noch pünktlich unter dem Weihnachtsbaum 🎄hat!!! Ist das was? Ja, das ist geil!  PS: Am besten schaut ihr euch mal den Fortis YouTube-Kanal und Website (fortis-swiss.com) an und kleiner Tipp: Die Chancen steigen natürlich, wenn ihr überall folgt und den Newsletter noch abonniert.
 Achtung: Gewinnspiel wird nicht von Instagram organisiert und steht in keinem Zusammenhang mit Instagram. Eine Bargeldauszahlung des Gewinns ist nicht möglich. Der Rechtsweg ist ausgeschlossen. Ausführliche Gewinnspielbedingungen unter: https://www.fortis-swiss.com/de/the-malmedie-x-fortis-by giveaway-the-rules/  #fortis #fortiswatches #novonaut #partnership #watchesofinstagram #instawatch #watches #watch

This was 'Blood Swept Lands and Seas of Red', an art installation at the Tower of London consisting of 888,246 ceramic poppies - one for each British and Colonial soldier who died during the war. It commemorated the 100th year since Britain's first day in the First World War. The first poppy was planted on the 5th August, with the 888,246th poppy being planted on 11th November 2014. Each of the poppies was sold to charity raising millions for six associated charities. It is now 105 years since the armistice was signed between the Allies and Germany, ceasing a war in which an estimated 37,000,000 people died. #remembranceday #toweroflondon

Photo by @melissafarlow // @TheBlueParadox at Chicago’s Museum of Science and Industry is an very cool, immersive experience about the environment. The mission is to educate and inspire us all to do our part collectively and reduce plastic in our oceans that impacts the planet. It’s engaging and fun experience for all ages, yet you leave and think about the message.  The show features photos by @randyolson - and across the hall is a fabulous exhibit about shrinking glaciers by my friend James Balog - titled Extreme Ice. @randyolson @theblueparadox @msichicago @james_balog @thephotosociety

@melissafarlow // It was shocking to go from an inspiring exhibit at the Museum of Science and Industry called The Blue Paradox featuring photos by @randyolson and many others work addressing issues of plastic pollution and climate change … AND walk outside into Chicago bathed in brown smoke from wildfires making it the most polluted air in any city in the world. I never thought I’d live to see climate change.  @randyolson @theblueparadox @msichicago @thephotosociety

Una relación de pareja no es lo que la mayoría piensa que es. No se despierta uno cada mañana para hacer el desayuno y comer juntos. No son abrazos eternos en la cama y palabras dulces hasta que los dos se duerman. No es una casa limpia llena de risas y amor todos los días. No es perfección.
Una relación de pareja es alguien que te roba la manta en mitad de la noche. Es a veces mal genio y palabras duras. Es estar de pronto y obstinadamente en desacuerdo, aceptar los momentos silenciosos hasta que los corazones se curen y perdonen. Es llegar a casa y encontrar a la misma persona todos los días, es monotonía. Es ropa sucia y camas sin hacer. Es orgullo cuando se trata de razones.
Es tragarse las molestas palabras en lugar de decirlas en voz alta para no lastimar al otro.
Pero en esas amargas experiencias se encuentran los más bellos regalos. Una relación de pareja es tener en tu vida a alguien que se preocupa por ti a pesar de qué y quién eres, a pesar de tus errores e imperfecciones.
Es alguien que ayuda en este duro trabajo de la vida. Es colaboración mutua, hacerse la cena entre los dos y sentarse juntos, a una hora tardía, porque los dos tuvieron un día loco. Es tener una crisis emocional y que tu pareja se acueste contigo y te sostenga, y te diga que todo va a estar bien. Y tú le creas.
Se trata de seguir amando a alguien a pesar de que a veces te vuelve absolutamente loco.
Amar a alguien no siempre es fácil, a veces es muy difícil. Pero es increíble y reconfortante. Una de las mejores cosas que alguna vez vas a experimentar en la vida. Texto @kokuhga

news flash: last week, just north of cabo near our hotel in baja, a mama sea turtle came ashore to lay a clutch of eggs. she made three nests, spending ~20 minutes in each (the first and last nest are visible in the second video) and used her fins to push sand and bury herself deeper into the sand before laying the eggs, before making her way back to the ocean and vanishing into a wave. according to the man in this video, the eggs should hatch in 1-2 months and the turtles (loggerheads) lay several nests in order to maximize reproductive output + help protect the eggs from predators 🐢

“conflict in congo is like a babushka (matryoshka) doll....you have conflicts sitting inside conflicts....it’s about local issues, who controls land, which chief is in power....often linked to ethnicity, because at local level ethnicity is the principle organizer of politics....at the next level, it is national power, partially due to collapse of mobutu and effects of belgian colonialism....but there it is more about using ethnicity to leverage a better position in parliament or a piece of a smuggling racket in gold....then you have the regional power politics, which mainly involves rwanda and that role really began in 1994 with the rwandan genocide....the conflict initially was not about minerals, though they became important over time to fund war efforts, esp for a country like rwanda that is small and poor....but when tantalum shot through the roof, which happened to be at a time of extreme violence, it began to shift incentives of those involved in the conflict and it was no longer about national security....around 2000 the various actors became more invested in minerals....but the war here is really about power and access to power, and that passes through local politicians. so you need to understand the politics” - jason stearns

*note: the above may serve to help understand the “conflict in congo,” the atmosphere inside the country, and is not meant to address the past/current influence of foreign powers “outside”

In the silence of nature. I’ve envisioned this moment for more than six years. Ever since I first saw this scene, I wanted to capture it in a certain way. On this beautiful morning, I finally captured the vista I wanted. A person was watching me through the thick mist and gave the final piece a sense of scale and solitude.
Captured with Nikon Z7 II and Nikkor Z 70-200 f/2.8 S.

I’m thrilled to welcome you to my new exhibition ’In the Solitude of Nature’ in Helsinki. Location is Finnfoto Gallery in the Redi shopping centre 2nd floor. 

‘In the Solitude of Nature’ is a photography exhibition that showcases Nordic landscapes and atmospheric moments. Capturing unforgettable landscapes from the morning mist to the darkness of night. The images do not just capture places; they capture emotions, bringing you closer to the silence of nature. Featuring 34 of my photographs from the Nordics. 

The exhibition is open from 1.8. to 30.8.2023. Free entry.

Lost in the moment. A series of my favourite captures from Spain with the Nikon Z 8 and Z lenses. You can now see the video of me and some of my philosophy for photography on @nikoneurope Youtube channel. I was one of nine creators, who embarked on a bus trip from Malaga to Valencia in search of the perfect shot the new Z 8 mirrorless camera.
Packing a host of Z 9 features into a lightweight body, the all-new Z 8 gives image-makers an astounding flexibility to bring our vision to life! 
With its impressive blend of class-leading performance and compact build, this camera is an exciting follow up to the Z 9 and the creative successor to the D850. The Z 8 is a video and stills powerhouse, with key new features such as an in-camera 12-bit RAW for video up to 8.3K/60p or 4.1K/120p, and an array of file sizes and burst speeds for still shooters. 
This is the perfect hybrid camera for creators who want a lighter body for shooting handheld or a full-frame camera that will balance perfectly on any rig, including most gimbals. 
I can't wait for you all to be able to experience this camera and its impressive new features for yourselves!

Hoy por fin he tenido un rato para pasar las fotos de Vietnam de la cámara al ordenador. Y por unos instantes mi mente estuvo en esta piscina donde todos nos bañábamos mientras llovía y llovía.

No fui capa de aguantar la cámara sin retirarme un poco, estaba en sitio seguro pero el tren pasa tan cerca que impresiona. Esta vía de tren tiene más de 120 años y atraviesa una de las calles de la capital de Vietnam.

Ahora que estamos acabando nuestro recorrido por algunas provincias de Vietnam, sin duda el distrito de Mai Chau, ubicado en el noroeste, ha sido de mis favoritos. Rodeado de montañas y arrozales, las aldeas están formadas por viviendas humildes cuyos campesinos trabajando la tierra son un símbolo de identidad del país, además de una de las principales fuentes de sustento.

Travel isn’t just about new places, new people, and new experiences, its also a soul searching adventure - on which I am hooked!

My latest adventure takes me to Eastern Canada, starting in Montréal, Québec.  My driving route will follow le fleuve Saint-Laurent (Saint Lawrence River) to Québec City, and onto Québec’s spectacular Gaspesie (Gaspé Peninsula), before I drive further east to Canada’s four Maritime provinces - New Brunswick, Nova Scotia, Prince Edward Island, and Newfoundland & Labrador.

Today’s photo feature was taken at la Roche Percé (Percé Rock), one of Québec’s most iconic natural wonders, on the easternmost tip of the Gaspesie.  More updates to come, as I continue to Canada’s Atlantic coast.

#travel #perce #gaspesie #quebec #canada

I did it!!! I’ve finally fulfilled my long standing dream to drive to the great Arctic Ocean.  I drove not one, but BOTH of North America’s ONLY two roads to reach the Arctic seas - once via Alaska’s #DaltonHighway to Deadhorse / Prudhoe Bay, and once via Canada’s #DempsterHighway to its NEW northern terminus of Tuktoyaktuk in Canada’s Northwest Territories (highway just opened in 2017).⠀
⠀
These are among North America’s most treacherous and dangerous roads, and were both my BEST and WORST travel experiences ever!  I look forward to sharing more of my Arctic adventures with you in the days and weeks ahead.⠀
⠀
#travel #adventuretravel #arctic #alaska #deadhorse #prudhoebay #yukon #nwt #inuvik #tuktoyaktuk

With my daughter enrolled in public school this year, this is the first year in 6 years that we aren't in Baja during February. I miss the warm weather and being outside every day in the sun but we've still been getting out here in Utah to re-engage with winter and give it another chance. We've been sledding, winter hiking, going to the climbing gym, and teaching my daughter to ski on the weekends. It has been fun but I still prefer the Baja winter life. We decide to enroll Zoey in one more year it public school. She has good teachers and friends which has been great for her but after that are thinking of resuming home schooling and once again returning to Baja for the winter.

For the past 6 years, I’ve mostly been spending my winters in Baja. In some ways fallen out of love with the long cold days of winter but with my daughter in school and will be for at least one more year, it is time for me to give winter a second chance. This hike up Angels Landing in Zion was a good reminder of how great winter hiking is. This hike is normally so crowded, but during the early morning hours in winter on a snowy day? Hardly anyone and the views are stunning with the yellow, red and orange cliffs covered in winter fluffy snow. I don’t know if I’ll ever hike it again in the summer but during the winter? Absolutely.

Chasing dreams beneath the waves: after countless hours, I finally speared a Yellowtail and it was a beauty. 30lbs and 51” inches which is longer than my 6 year old daughter is tall. From sashimi on the beach to a New Year’s Prosecco and Panettone trade to a freeze full of fish to enjoy for months, this catch is more than just a trophy—it’s a memory that still has me riding high.

I'm a Utah boy who grew up far from the ocean. I never really had a relationship with it and never really felt comfortable in it but over the past 5 years of coming to Baja where I taught myself to Freedive and spearfish that relationship has grown and given me a much deeper appreciation for what's under the water that covers 71% of our planet. Spearfishing has been my reason to spend a few hours every day in the water, mostly watching and observing the behavior of the sea life and in the right place when something special unexpectedly swims by. A few days ago I shot my biggest fish to date, shown here, which is a 28lbs Leopard Grouper. This fish is delicious, which was processed and put in the freezer so it can feed us for a number of days once we get back to Utah: 👌

Merry Christmas everyone. We took off for Zoey’s school break and came down to Baja for the holidays. So much to be grateful for here but I think our favorite aspect of being in Baja, especially this trip without the van, is just being outside all day, every day, from sunrise to after sunset. Feel good to be alive and sharing this life with my favorite humans.

It's the slow life for me now.

Just a few years ago, I traveled from country to country, experiencing something new every week, every day, every minute. I was filled with impressions and experiences, which I cherish deeply and will keep remembering them forever. But I came to realize that the true essence of travel isn't just about the landscapes or the sights.

It's about connections. The kind that grows stronger the longer you stay, becoming a part of communities. Of families.

Mongolia taught me this valuable lesson, and there's no looking back.

#Benİstersem No 02 İrem Çapar, 2000 yılında Hatay’ın Fidanlı köyünde doğdu. Ailesi çiftçi. İrem 10 yaşındayken babası “Kızım bak annen sana yetişemiyor, çok hareketlisin. Spor salonunda en azından enerjini atarsın” diyerek onu boks kursuna yazdırdı. İrem ayağı kanayana dek kum torbasına tekme attı. Antrenörü @cemal_daglioglu dinlenmesini söylediğinde “Dinlenmek istemiyorum, devam edeceğim” diyordu. Yara kabuk tutuyor ama İrem her antrenmanda yarayı yeniden kanatıyordu. Ayağında hâlâ o yaranın izleri var. İrem’e “Bu erkek sporu, kızlar yapamaz. Niye yapıyorsun bu sporu? Kaslanacaksın, çok çirkin görüneceksin. Kadın sporu değil bu, sana zarar verir. Sen erkek gibi mi olmaya çalışıyorsun?” diyen komşular, bir yandan da İrem’in annesini dolduruyorlardı. Salona gelip giden bir çocuk sürekli İrem’le dalga geçiyor, “Bu sporu niye yapıyorsun? Dünya şampiyonu olacağını mı sanıyorsun? Senden dünya şampiyonu olur mu?” diyordu.
İrem 2013 ve 2014’te Dünya MuayThai Şampiyonası’nda dünya şampiyonu oldu. 2016’da Türkiye Bayanlar Ferdi Boks Şampiyonası ve Türkiye Gençler Kick Boks Şampiyonası’nda altın madalya aldı. 2017’de MuayThai Gençler Dünya Şampiyonası’nda çok zorlu rakipleri yenerek bir kez daha dünya şampiyonu oldu. Mustafa Kemal Üniversitesi Beden Eğitimi Öğretmenliği bölümünde okurken, gelecekte küçük bir salon açıp köydeki kız çocuklarını spora başlatmanın hayalini kuruyor ve şöyle diyor: “Kız çocukları inandıkları uğruna mücadele etmeli; her zaman umut olduğunu bilmeli ve hedefe giden yolda önlerine çıkan hiçbir engelin onları durdurmasına izin vermemeli. Kız çocukları güçlendikçe toplum da güçlenir, İnsanların önyargıları kırılabilir. Bunu başarmak mümkün. Kız çocukları yeter ki bunu istesinler.”
Devamı kitapta !

Very happy to be at Milan Fashion Week for Brunello Cucinelli’s Ladies Fall/Winter 2024/25 collection presentation. 
I was very happy to meet with Mr Brunello, his family including his daughters Camilla and Carolina who told me more about the brand’s story and this season’s inspiration.
The collection highlighted the brands commitment to style with intricate detail and superb quality.
I saw many beautiful pieces using a wide variety of different materials and craftsmanship creating a collection that also gave a feeling of consistency that stayed true to Brunello Cucinelli’s DNA and I just want to try on everyone every piece. 
This was also a special event as it’s the first time Mr Lee has attended a fashion presentation with me 😊

Sometimes there’s mystery in what draws us to things, people or places… With Oahu, I can’t quite put my finger on it.  I tried to explain it in an earlier post. I won’t try again 😀 A few weeks ago I took a helicopter ride over this island I love so much. I’d done that several times before, but not right over the Ko’olau Range, and not during sunset. Wowzers! I was feeling so happy and grateful, thanks @magnum_helicopters for showing me something I’d never seen before and giving me one more reason to love this place!  I’m glad the island didn’t get hit by a missile.🚀(!) I’m curious to hear people’s reflections on how it felt to sit in that mental space for 30 minutes until it became clear it was a false alarm? I was not on the Island, and only heard about it after I knew it was not true. Today I saw death threats were being made against the worker who made the mistake. 😒I guess we know that a crisis always brings out the worst in people, but I bet it also brings out the best. Hoping to read some positivity here. 🙂

For the longest time I’ve been satisfied and chill - not really wanting more from life. 🤙 Just at peace with how I am and how the world is. 🌏 But lately I’ve felt like I want to learn and grow… I’m feeling like my teenage self again, when I was excited about picking up a new  book or a new idea. I think this mostly came from friends who inspired  me… They know who they are. Feeling very grateful for this change, and for the people who got my creative mojo firing. Onwards and upwards! 🚀

This shot was from yesterday’s hike on Kauai! ⛰Was moving so fast with my time-limited hiking partners that I never got a chance to take out my camera! This was shot on the iPhone 7+ and edited with built-in Apple tools and some Snapseed. After all that, I brought it into Photoshop to remove some purple noise in the shadows. Finally I made a few changes to clarity and color in IGs editor. Haha. Imagine the day when your phone camera could do everything a DSLR can do… It’s really not that far away. In many ways, the phone is better — certainly for portability and also in the way it handles different layers of depth and light. I know if I shot this on my DSLR it would have been even harder for me to process to my satisfaction. Went for a more painterly feel since it was pretty noisy and easier to edit that way?? I like it a lot !! Do you like?? :-) 😀

One of my favorite New Year’s Eve displays ever was in Singapore—as amazing as the country itself! 🇸🇬 This shot was just a regular old night before the fireworks, but I am trying to decide where to go for a fireworks this year... any suggestions? What’s the coolest place you’ve seen for NYE? 🔥

I was surprised how many people responded to what I wrote yesterday and glad to know people found comfort in my thoughts. 🙏 Often this feeling of being “lost” comes from a larger cultural context. I just got back from Bhutan, a place where life feels integrated, whole, directed. About 7 years ago, I chose to live in multiple places around the world; I consider myself a member of various communities. The differences are striking. One of my favorite homes is Hawaii. 🏝Tomorrow I’m going there.🤙Part of why I love Hawaii and why it feels like home to me is similar to the feeling I get in Bhutan. There’s an attitude of calm in Hawaii. You see it in everything, from the speed of traffic, to the gait with which people walk. 👣In part, it’s island life, but it runs deeper than geography. It’s cultural and philosophical. When your community is strong, your purpose in life feels more secure. 💕The state of Hawaii is ranked lowest in the US for depression. 😀It’s fifth lowest for separation and divorce. 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦Is this all because of sunny weather and beautiful beaches? I don’t think so. It helps, but that’s not the whole story. There’s a saying or hashtag you may have seen on Instagram #luckywelivehawaii To me, that simple idea reflects pride, gratitude, and wisdom, all in one concept: pride in heritage and traditions, gratitude for that heritage to exist and continue, and wisdom of those living in Hawaii to recognize the uniqueness that their heritage does exist and continue. 🌏😎When you exist in a community like that, you’re less likely to suffer as an individual. If you’re struggling on a personal level, sometimes the answer may lie outside yourself—in a community that’s waiting for you. Aloha :) 🏄‍♂️

Lately I’ve been meeting a lot of “lost” people that seem to suffer from a crisis of confidence. I’m trying to help where I can. You don’t always have to understand the path forward. It’s OK to be lost at times. Crisis begets growth. In fact, some research shows that crisis is one of the few things that can really change us after age 25. If you’re feeling this way, just know that things can change in a moment — a chance occurrence can change your life forever. In the meantime, fill your brain with good ideas, follow the signs that life is sending to you, be open to what’s possible. If you’re doing OK in life right now, give your smile and empathy to strangers and friends. We never know what someone is going through.  What does all this have to do with this photo? Haha well, I suppose this photo gives me a feeling of hope and a reminder that life, despite its conflicts, is always a beautiful thing. 😀🌎📷🤙
Playing with my drone in The Maldives 🇲🇻 🤗

This place felt like a dream; the more I visit a place, usually I want to move on, and see some place new. With this river, not far from Cebu, I want to go back! Visiting the Philippines, it feels like you discover more and more every time. I guess that’s how things work when a country has 7,000 islands! This spot is fairly well known…. Just imagine what’s out there the more you explore. I’ve been asking my friends lately… Why do you travel? 🌎For me, it started through photography. Before photography, I mostly wanted to live in foreign places—I wasn’t big into visiting or sightseeing; I was never much of a traveller until I picked up a camera. 📷 I’m curious to hear your thoughts. 🤔  BTS:FYI: another shot from my Google Pixel phone (not the new one).

Rinpung Monastery, Paro, Bhutan. A “dzong” is the word they use  in Bhutan for a fortress/monastery. These beautiful structures with giant walls reveal a lot about Bhutan’s unique culture. First, it is a defensible fortress--a holdover from days when wars were still happening. You can’t see from the picture I took here, but the walls descend further, so there’s no way for attackers to climb up or get inside. There’s tiny slits  around the Dzong where people inside can shoot arrows at attackers on the outside! 🏹I’ve seen 10 fortresses like this in throughout Bhutan, and they’re usually built on a hillside with a strategic view of the valley, and, if the view isn’t so great, there’s a secondary watchtower in a better position. But what are they defending? I am just learning, but there’s a unique confluence of activity inside each Dzong: besides a military fortress, today, Dzong’s are homes for monks, and a spiritual center, but they also house all kinds of offices—think of it like the combination church, DMV, a civil court, an architecture planning office, and anything else related to the city’s administration. It shows how there is a lack of separation between “church and state”… In Bhutan, their philosophical and “religious” beliefs (some say Buddhism is not a religion, but a philosophical perspective), are integrated with the government, not separated. 🎊More Bhutanese are beginning to dress like Westerners, but when you visit the Dzong, you are required to where the traditional dress of the Bhutanese people. To foreign eyes, it makes for a colorful and exciting experience—you feel like you’re in the 16th century watching the activity inside, even though people might be there to get architectural plans approved, or to get a divorce, or something else that seems very “modern” to us. Ah yes, and the chilis… I had to include the chilis drying in the sun. Bhutanese add chilis to almost every dish (even in their rice); certainly there will be chilis in every meal! The chilis are dried outside, typically on the roof of homes. 🏠 Drying can take a month! ☀️I think I’ll be adding chilis to dishes when i get back home! 😀

Tiger’s Nest, Bhutan. 🇧🇹 When I first told people I was planning a trip to Bhutan, very few knew what I was talking about. 🤔Where? What? For those that did know Bhutan, it was always for one of two things: 1) the pleasant idea that the government and King make policy decisions based on the principles of “Gross National Happiness” and 2) the Himalayan Buddhist temple, Tiger’s Nest which I’ve posted here. I’d seen photos of Tiger’s Nest for many years, but photos do not give you a sense of just how high up it is! 🌄📷 I’d had the impression that Tiger’s Nest was perched just above a city, and that you could look up and see it from a town below, sort of like the Potala Palace in Lhasa. That’s not the case - not even close! You’ll probably never see a photo of Tiger’s Nest from the valley floor on Instagram because it would be so boring—in a photo taken from the bottom, Tiger’s Nest would be just a tiny speck on the mountain side. 🗻For Americans or anyone who has been to Yosemite, imagine you’re standing on the valley floor and looking at the very tops of the highest rock surfaces and you see a small speck that *might* be manmade. That’s the best way I could relate to you how high up this special Bhutanese monastery is.  To visit the viewpoint from where I took this photo, you start at a forested valley floor, and hike up several hours. 🚶🏻🏃🏻‍♀️There’s no rock climbing involved, and its only steep in a few places, but the sheer length of the trek makes the existence of this place that much more remarkable. It’s not just its beauty and the seemingly impossible engineering that gives you a sense of awe,  it’s also the idea that every piece of wood, stone, every relic and jewel housed inside, was carried up one by one. 💪 Pro Tip: If you decided to visit yourself, start your journey before dawn, or in the afternoon, and you’re likely to have the viewpoint all to yourself. We did :) !! We were there so late, we came down in total darkness. Remember your flashlights.

One of my favorite drone perspectives of my stay at the the @conrad_maldives ; can you see that little rectangle sticking out from the bottom bungalow? Thats an underwater restaurant! 🏝I was dreaming of the Maldives warm shores the last few nights! 🌌I just spent some of the coldest nights of my life in a mountain village in Bhutan!  Its been an eye opening trip here in the land of the Thunder Dragon—I have learned to not take life’s luxuries for granted: a warm, soft place to sleep; a heater or fire on a chilly night, or even a bathroom inside your house. All things I’ve taken for granted since birth. No longer! I can say I’m glad to have toughed it out sleeping with the same bedding as the locals, but when I come back to Bhutan I will definitely bring a sleeping bag!  I’ve had very little Internet here, so I can’t yet upload the video for the Maldives trip giveaway, but its coming soon 😀

Belle journée 💜

RECETTE 🍪 

Cookies IG bas

Ingrédients secs :
👩‍🍳190g de poudre d’amandes
👩‍🍳1 càs de bicarbonate alimentaire 
👩‍🍳Une pincée de fleur de sel 
👩‍🍳120g de bon chocolat noir coupé en grosses pépites 
Ingrédients humides :
👩‍🍳2 càs d’huile de coco solide et juste ramollie, désodorisée 
👩‍🍳Quelques gouttes d’extrait de vanille 
👩‍🍳1 gros œuf
👩‍🍳2 càs de sirop d’agave

👩‍🍳Préchauffer le four à 190°C, mode chaleur tournante si possible.
👩‍🍳Couper au couteau les pépites de chocolat, afin.
👩‍🍳Dans un grand saladier, mélanger les ingrédients humides : battre énergiquement l’huile de coco ramollie avec le sirop d’agave au fouet. Ajouter l’oeuf, la vanille et fouetter bien.
👩‍🍳Dans un autre saladier, mélanger les ingrédients secs à la cuillère : poudre d’amandes et bicarbonate puis les 120g de pépites de chocolat et le sel.
👩‍🍳Verser les ingrédients secs sur les ingrédients humides et mélanger rapidement avec une cuillère à soupe ou une maryse, sans trop insister.
👩‍🍳Sur une plaque recouverte de papier sulfurisé, disposer des petites boules de pâte en les espaçant bien. 
👩‍🍳Enfourner pour 7 à 8 minutes à 190°C (selon la taille des cookies et le four). Pour moi, 7 minutes dans le four préchauffé pour 10 cookies. 

Bonne régalade 😋

CHANDELEUR 🥞

Crêpes IG bas

Ingrédients
🥞 150 g de farine intégrale de petit épeautre
🥞 300 g de lait d’avoine
🥞 2 œufs

Préparation
🥞 Dans un saladier, battez les œufs en omelette.
🥞 Délayez en versant 1/3 du lait.
🥞 Versez la farine dans le saladier et mélangez bien pour l’incorporer au mélange.
🥞 Ajouter progressivement le reste du lait, en fouettant bien avec la cuillère pour éviter les grumeaux.
🥞 Laissez reposer 30 minutes. 
🥞 Faites chauffer une poêle antiadhésive avec un peu d’huile de coco.
🥞 A l’aide d’une louche versez la pâte et répartissez dans la poêle. Faîtes cuire les crêpes de chaque côté quelques minutes.

Bonne régalade 😋

PETITE GOURMANDISE 😋

Macaron chocolat 
👩‍🍳150 g de sucre glace
👩‍🍳90 g de poudre d’amande
👩‍🍳15 g de cacao en poudre
👩‍🍳2 blancs d’oeufs moyens ou 3 petits (75 g en tout)
👩‍🍳10 g de sucre (glace ou normal)
👩‍🍳100 g de chocolat noir à pâtisser
👩‍🍳10 cl de crème liquide
👩‍🍳20 g de beurre

👩‍🍳Tamisez plusieurs fois le sucre, le cacao et la poudre d’amande pour obtenir un mélange très fin.
👩‍🍳Montez les blancs en neige très ferme. Lorsqu’ils commencent à être fermes, ajouter le sucre glace (les 10 grammes), en 2 fois.
👩‍🍳Ajoutez les blancs à la poudre (cacao/amande/sucre) et mélangez pour obtenir une pâte lisse, brillante.
👩‍🍳A l’aide d’une poche à douille, réalisez des petits cercles sur une feuille de papier sulfurisé ou une plaque de silicone.
👩‍🍳Laissez “pocher” à l’air libre 20 minutes.
👩‍🍳Préchauffez le four a 150°C.
👩‍🍳Enfournez les macarons 20 minutes (15 min si ce sont des petits macarons).
👩‍🍳Réalisez la ganache en faisant chauffer la crème et en la versant sur le chocolat en morceaux. Mixer, puis rajouter le beurre, mixer à nouveau et réserver au frais.
👩‍🍳Sortez les macarons, laissez-les refroidir quelques minutes, décollez-les et garnissez-les.

Bonne dégustation 😋

The Sau reservoir was built in the sixties to store water from the Ter river and supply the metropolitan area of Barcelona. During its construction the water covered the old town of Sant Romá de Sau, including its church tower, which has now re-surfaced with the drought.

El pantano de Sau se construyó en los años sesenta para almacenar agua del río Ter y abastecer al área metropolitana de Barcelona. Durante su construcción el agua cubrió el antiguo pueblo de Sant Romá de Sau, incluida la torre de su iglesia, y ahora con la sequía vuelve a la superficie.

Today is my 35th birthday! I’ve been fortunate enough to spend several birthdays in some of Mother Earth’s truly majestic locations while surrounded by luminous souls. I remember acknowledging to myself as little as two years ago while I trekked and camped in Patagonia for my 33rd birthday about how I was experiencing the most surreal birthday I’ve ever had as snow fell on my face and melted away while hiking at the end of the earth. 

Well, I’m now a girl dad of a 6 month old and have a growing family of my own. No adventure has ever come close to this one I’m currently experiencing. I’m ecstatic that at age 35 I now truly see that my life has really just begun. Thank you for being a part of this life journey with me. Here’s to many more adventures for all of us in the not so distant future. ♥️🗺🙏🏽

Verás todos los detalles sobre este proyecto fotográfico en @viveandalucia

¿Conocías el norte de Alemania?

Apunta estos sitios porque poco se conoce del norte de Alemania.a ruta fue durante 4 días.

• Ciudad de Lübeck, donde sus calles te remontan a una época medieval, arquitectura de ladrillo gótico y su emblemática puerta de Holsten.

• Husum, más al norte ya en la frontera con Dinamarca, una preciosa ciudad con su puerto para pasar un día recorriendo sus calles.

• Isla de Sylt, podrás llegar en tren, la mayor de las islas Frisias, playas kilométricas, bosques, faros y sus casas con tejados de caña.

Apuntaló en tu lista, una Alemania desconocida para muchos en la que desconectar. 
En destacados de mi perfil tienes el viaje completo!

La experiencia de estar en un lugar donde desconectar y de la forma que el impacto al medio ambiente sea menor.
Mi gran descubrimiento ha sido el norte de Alemania, casi en la frontera con Dinamarca. Trasladándome desde Lubeck en tren.
Las tres partes que he visitado esta vez han sido:

- Lübeck: Destaca por la arquitectura, el estilo medieval y el estilo gótico.

- Husum: Un pueblo costero con unas calles y unas casas preciosas.

- Sylt: La mayor de las Islas frisias, playas interminables, faros y los mejores atardeceres.

Gracias a @germanytourism @visitluebeck @husum.nordfriesland

Cada día se reinicia un año.

No se si será la mejor fotografía de los últimos 365 días, pero tengo claro es lo mucho que disfruté bajo la nieve ese día.
Hace un par de días pensaba en todas las personas que desde principios de año han estado luchando, luchando por sobrevivir, por mantener su puesto de trabajo, por nuestra salud, por estar alegres, por seguir aquí...
Todos somos luchadores en algún sentido, incluso cuando las cosas van mal.
A esos luchadores que no descansan nunca, GRACIAS, gracias una vez más.

Si tuviera que resumir mi año, os podría contar cientos, algunas de ellas tristes, otras llenas de felicidad, pero todas ellas tienen algo en común, y es algo tan simple como sonreír.

Sonreír, sonreír a las personas que nos rodean, las conozcamos o no, sonreírle a la vida, sonreír ante los problemas que nos parecen imposibles de solucionar.
Es solo un gesto que con la ayuda de la mirada transmite bienestar.

Aunque instagram ha cambiado mucho en los últimos años, para peor en mi parecer. Logra sacar en muchas ocasiones facilitar el crecimiento personal, para bien y para mal, el ego, y sobre todo darle fuerza a la autoestima de los que valoran los likes y la venta de vidas idílicas que os prometo que no existen.

A todos vosotros que habéis llegado hasta el final del escrito, sonrie y vive una vida real.

PD: Hace unos días propuse una de mis ilusiones, regalar a alguien la opción de decidir que tipo de foto sería la última del año y regalarle una impresión en grande, sta es la foto de Japón que @oscar_penelo le gustaría tener.
Instagram decidió no enseñar a todos los Stories.

Os deseo un feliz año y a seguir sonriendo siempre.

To date, I found stillness nights behind the doors of my soul.
In the morning rain on my way to work, happy drops as it soaks it to my bones and the moon looks at me askance.

Now´s the time to find out why all the things that I want to be.
They will arrive, just take patience.
Praise God for this little angel on earth. 🥹🙏🏼✨ #wheredoesthetimego

POV: You find out you have Basal Cell Skin Cancer.

SKIN CANCER WARNING: ⚠️ (graphic)
If you notice something changing or seemingly abnormal on your skin and it doesn’t go away within reasonable time.. get it checked!! I ignored this spot for nearly a year… although this damage was likely done years ago as a child or teen.. this was a great reminder to wear sunscreen and don’t over expose yourself to the sun. I hardly ever wore sunscreen growing up.. 🥵 I was outdoor most days, played soccer with my hair back in the boiling heat and in my early 20’s I soaked myself in tanning oil baking under the sun to be as dark as I could. I REPEAT: the sun is not bad for you. Get out in nature, breathe fresh air and soak up the natural benefits of the sun but for the love of God protect your skin! Once you have skin cancer you’re even more likely to produce it again, yearly checks and early detection is very important! 

A big thanks to @drthornwellparker at @skincancerconsultants for taking such great care of me! 🥹🙏🏼 I’ll keep you posted with the healing process! 

👉🏼 Have you had skin cancer? If so.. which kind… Does skin cancer run in your family?!

Part of my upcoming story on Zoroastrianism, the oldest monotheistic religion in the world, for @natgeo. Mehernosh, a pallbearer - the person in charge of carrying the dead body at a funeral - walks away from one of the two functioning towers of silence in Karachi.
A tower of silence, known as dakhma, is a circular structure built by Zoroastrians for excarnation - that means the exposure of human corpses to the elements for decomposition - in order to avoid contamination of the soil and other natural elements by the decomposing dead bodies. Carrion birds, usually vultures (though no longer in Karachi…) and other scavengers, consume the flesh. Skeletal remains are gathered into a central pit where further weathering and continued breakdown occurs. In this dakhma, reflective mirrors have been fitted inside the tower of silence to increase the heat and help the body decomposing faster.
Karachi, a city of 20 millions, has 800 Zoroastrians known as Parsees, 70% of them are above the age of 70 years old. #zoroastrianism #zoroastrian #towerofsilence #towersofsilence #parsi #parsee

I was in the dust with the wrestlers and I looked up and realised that a crowd had formed, a sea of shalwar kamiz. All these men (and 1 woman!! Can you spot her??) had gathered on the edge of a pilgrimage site to watch a spontaneous wrestling match - called Koshti or Malakhro in Baloch. With laughter and agitation, some theatre, it’s the ancestral raw version of the WWF stuff you might have unfortunately seen on TV. Pakistan, Baluchistan province.

I was in Karachi last March, city of 20 million, I love it there. On my pilgrimage in Baluchistan, I met a man who called himself Samundar Baba (Ocean Baba) - he owned boats. Unusual character, long beard and serious looking type, a big hashish smoker. He lived in Lyari, considered a dodgy area although I didn’t think so. I reached out and we met in his house. I was interested in this world of men you can find on fishing boats. So I asked him to bring me. This is the Korangi fishing harbor, one of the largest one in south asia. It can be complicated to photograph there because of authorisation and army nearby. Samundar kindly got me in and I spent a few hours jumping boats as the sun got low.

The original ravers were just getting started. Fun and mad times with the passionate Ishk Ali and his buddies, like Daula Sain. It was day 2 of our 12 days pilgrimage journey, walking together across Sindh and Baluchistan. That is a double cigarette and a sacrificial goat. Pakistan.

2023 is gone, just a number! It’s been a year filled with travels in Pakistan, Uzbekistan, Spain, Azerbaijan, Canada, Tajikistan, India etc…
It was interesting to meander through life between being a photographer, a farmer and be present for the family.
I thought of god a bit, all triggered by a story on Zoroastrianism for National Geographic magazine (coming up). How and why do we often inherit the feeling of being watched by God, god like a massive cctv system… religion the opium of the people?
Probably god is busy with a lot more than watching you… Is your god a vengeful one or a god that you will live with and whose law you must respect, like gravity? Lots of fun questions with no real need for answers..

Here is a serene scene, mixing all religious influences (at least to my eye!), in a place that has seen Animism, Buddhism, Zoroastrianism and more recently Islam (ismaili faith). It’s in an “ostone”, a shrine in Tajikistan’s Wakhan corridor, adorned with ibex and Marco Polo horns - and a triangle of stones for the “shirogh” (the candle of cotton dipped in oil), lit for special occasion (for Jumarat, Eid or for Didor, the birthday of the Aga Khan etc). Azom Khon, the caretaker, is praying for me before I leave. It was beautiful so I pulled back and took a picture.

I will be sharing pictures here from my recent travels until I leave for SE Asia on February 20th.
Love and light for 2024.

I saw him and jumped out of the Uaz and took his hand. We walked to his sheep, we had never met but he got the drift, hand in hand. The playful dog is called Kanash, and he is the great shepherd Mamedo Mamed, I took a note of it. The mountains dancing in the distance, it’s Dagestan in Russia (“Dag" means Mountains in Turkish). The Lezgins people here are so hospitable and kind, I was in the depth of Azerbaijan in the Caucasus mountains and it was beautiful, felt real. Thanks to dear @ntgarib for sharing her place of heart.

Photography is layers of understandings. Delighted to have one my images from an ongoing story on Zoroastrians selected by @natgeo for the National Geographic Pictures of the Year 2023 #NatGeoPOY2023

Here after a rough train ride we ended up in Jaqorgon, Uzbekistan, near the Afghan border. It was last July, crazy hot but the plov was delicious (rice, mutton, carrots, raisins, spices… the whole works!). 
After much research (it took weeks, thanks @just.laowai ) we found this family that welcomed us. Here, an all-woman ceremony beneath a hand-embroidered suzani marks a son’s departure to study in the capital, Tashkent. While the woman (partly hidden behind the veil, wearing green) leads the prayer, reciting Quranic verses, others remove a covering to bless the flatbread called nan. This ritual was influenced by Zoroastrianism, the world’s oldest monotheist religion. I added some images if you slide right, these were all shot that afternoon. Thanks to @jamesbwellford for sticking with it, @sadiequarrier wonder woman, @kristinromey @rabbitearz93 and many more at the Nat Geo office. One of the symbol on the suzani was borrowed from Zoroastrianism and symbolizes the 4 holy elements, fire, water, earth and air. @dimas.sarmangan

Thanks to @nasa astronaut @loralohara who I met today in space (via zoom), I got to look down at our amazing blue planet from the international space station, cruising amidst the cosmic ocean above us. 

Astronaut O’Hara, five months into a six month mission,  shared many insights about the fragility of our world, how borders vanish and natural systems connect, what life in zero gravity is like, the properties of water (droplets float), how planetary politics stay behind and much, much more. 
It blew my mind. 

The second image by @loralohara shows the entire Grand Canyon in all its eroded wonders in one single frame. It amazes me to think that it took me 71 days on foot to walk the length of that natural wonder, but the space station crosses it in seconds. 

Thanks again O’Hara and NASA for reminding us all the wonders we have not just in space, but right on our one shared home. 

#nightsky #space #spacestation #nasa #wonder #awe #grandcanyon #milkyway

To be honest the past year has been my absolute favorite year with Mason ever 🥰 What was the favorite age of your kids? 🤍 I feel 4 & 5 are such rewarding and enjoyable ages, so I will definitely enjoy this year to the fullest 💕

Austria Glimpse ✨
.
.
I finished my 4 day trip to Austria and it's surely been nothing less than surreal. Being at the places which I just saw in mobile wallpapers, even when I was staring at the structures, I wasn't able to believe if this was actually happening. As I walked through, I tried to absorb every sight, every curve on the building, every turn of the road, every small piece of it made me realize why I love to travel. Entering random streets, talking to locals, navigating through public transport, shopping through local groceries, trying to live the culture that has been passed on over the years to form the country what it is today. It's much more than just fancy pictures, these reels or my lame stories I've been spamming with, it's breathing this air and being here. I'd be travelling to four more places on this trip and I don't know which one I would find the best, but this surely made a place in my heart.
.
.
.
.

Union Station is Canada’s busiest, multi-modal passenger transportation hub, a designated national historic site and a significant part of Toronto’s history and identity. 

More than a quarter-million people use @torontounion daily. 

The @cityofto led Union Station’s revitalization with three objectives: to improve the quality and capacity of pedestrian movement, to restore heritage elements and to transform the Station into a major destination for shopping, dining and visiting #seetorontonow #wheretorontoisgoing
Sunrise #seetorontonow

Located 14 stories high - 200 feet above ground, lies an outdoor urban oasis, where @fairmontroyalyork garden grows. On any summer's day, @chef_jwfoster and the Planet 21 Team can be seen nurturing and tending to the vast variety of organic produce and herbs that are cared for without the use of herbicides and pesticides.

Fairmont also houses six beehives. It is the first of the Fairmont hives and is often noted as being the first rooftop apiary found at any hotel in the world. It was also the first to install a pollinator bee hotel in 2014, paving the way for more to follow in the following years. 

At its summer peak 350,000 honeybees reside in six beehives to produce an average of 450 pounds of honey per year. 

For almost 30 years, Fairmont Hotels has been committed to proactively protecting its local environments. 

A commitment to minimizing its impact on the planet.

Некоторым моим друзьям Мальдивы кажутся скучными, но наш отдых всегда получается не только расслабленный, но и насыщенный. Чем мы занимались в этот раз в @thenautilusisland 

🏊🏻‍♀️ Я много плавала - это моя любимая активность, а здесь к тому же и просто нереальный домашний риф 🐠
🏝 Устроили ужин на соседнем необитаемом острове 
🌠 Смотрели кино под звёздами 
🏸 Играли в теннис 
🍹Готовили коктейли

Some of my friends find the Maldives boring, but our vacation is always not only relaxed, but also eventful. What we did this time at @thenautilusisland

🏊🏻‍♀️ I swam a lot - this is my favorite activity, and here, besides, the house reef is simply unreal 🐠
🏝 We had dinner on a nearby uninhabited island
🌠 Watched a movie under the stars
🏸 Played tennis
🍹Prepared cocktails

Приехала в любимый остров-отель в @thenautilusisland 🏝 Идеальное место, чтобы отдохнуть с семьей: спокойно, уединённо. Очень нравится индивидуальный подход к каждому гостю: и к взрослым, и к детям. Кстати, анонсируют большую новую программу на апрель, думаю, может запланировать и на пасхальные каникулы тоже.  My favorite island hotel @thenautilusisland 🏝 A perfect place to relax with family, especially with a small child: calm, secluded. I really like the individual approach to each guest: both adults and children. By the way, they are announcing a big new program for April, I really think to plan it for the Easter holidays too.

Жемчуг является одним из основных декоративных элементов в коллекции, он ассоциируется со светлым образом Царевны и, конечно, с русским кодом. Из него выполнены аксессуары – сумки, украшения, лифы, оплечья и целое платье.
 
Pearls are one of the main decorative elements in the collection, associated with Ludmila’s image - a bright feminine beginning, and, of course, with the Russian code. They are used in accessories - bags, ornaments, bodices, shoulder pieces, and an entire dress.
 
#alenaakhmadullina @alenaakhmadullina_store #bricsfashionsummit

Многообразие образов сказки Пушкина в коллекции тяготеет к двум полюсам: женское начало, которое воплощает Людмила, проявляется в палитре светлых оттенков в сочетании с россыпями жемчуга в декоре и принтах, а мужское – Руслан и Черномор – в брутальных вещах из кожи и денима и четких структурах.
 
 
The diversity of fairy tale characters in the collection gravitates towards two poles: the feminine principle embodied by Ludmila is manifested in a palette of light shades combined with a scattering of pearls in decor and prints, whereas the masculine - Ruslan and Chernomor - is represented in rugged leather and denim items and clear structures.
 
#alenaakhmadullina @alenaakhmadullina_store #bricsfashionsummit

Кутюрная часть коллекции – это тизер будущей линии Alena Akhmadullina Couture, которую мы представим весной. Кутюрные платья ручной работы с вышивкой по шелковой сетке с использованием натурального жемчуга и богемского бисера. На каждое платье ушло до 100 часов работы. 

The couture part of the collection, consisting of 10 dresses, is a teaser of the upcoming regular Alena Akhmadullina Couture line. It features hand-made couture dresses with embroidery done with a Luneville hook on a silk mesh using natural nacreous pearls and Bohemian beads. Each dress took up to 100 hours of work. 

#alenaakhmadullina @alenaakhmadullina_store #bricsfashionsummit

Обувная линия выполнена в коллаборации с лабораторией Nature Based Lab, основной миссией которой является симбиоз экологических материалов и искусства. Специально для показа были созданы фактуры из биоразлагаемых материалов, вдохновленные сказкой «Руслан и Людмила»: например, фраза об «избушке на курьих ножках» навела на мысль об использовании яичной скорлупы для биопластика, а эпизоды, где похищенная Черномором Людмила гуляет в садах среди апельсиновых деревьев, вдохновили на эксперименты с применением сырья этого растения.

The footwear line, created in collaboration with the Nature Based Lab, whose main mission is the symbiosis of ecological materials and art, is worth special attention. Textures were created from biodegradable materials specifically for the show, inspired by the fairy tale «Ruslan and Ludmila»: for instance, the phrase about the «hut on chicken legs» led to the idea of using eggshells for bioplastics, and the episodes where Ludmila, kidnapped by Chernomor, walks in gardens among orange trees, inspired experiments with the raw materials of this plant.

@naturebasedlab
#alenaakhmadullina @alenaakhmadullina_store #bricsfashionsummit

Эскизный этап принтов с изображениями сказочного леса и неведомых зверей был выполнен с помощью искусственного интеллекта, а затем скетчи дорабатывались вручную.

The prints with the motifs of the enchanted forest and unknown beasts were initially designed using artificial intelligence, then sketches were manually refined.

Сказка начинается с приглашения в Лукоморье: волшебное пространство, где растет сказочный дуб. Его листья реализованы в объемной вышивке, выложены жемчугом, выполнены из сложенных в несколько слоев органзы.

The fairy tale begins with an invitation to Lukomorie: a magical space where a fantastical oak grows. Its leaves are realized in voluminous embroidery, laid out with pearls and made from organza folded in several layers.

#alenaakhmadullina @alenaakhmadullina_store #bricsfashionsummit

Have you reached your 2023 goals? 👀

I have achieved some, got close to others, and completely missed some.

And that’s completely fine. After all, it’s not about reaching goals but who you have to become to reach them. 🌱✨

For example:
🧊 I wanted to take a 5-minute cold shower daily but missed 15 days during the year. 
📚 I wanted to read 100 books but ended up reading 76.
📽 I wanted to reach 378K YouTube views with Beyond Sapiens, but we ended up with 339,161.

What matters is to actually set goals for yourself, your mind, body, and work, not because of vanity metrics but so that you wake up with a great sense of purpose every single day of the year.

The last 12 months have been filled with incredible growth, learning, and discovery. There was also a lot of emotional pain and failures, which, as much as unpleasant, is needed to grow into a new, evolved version of yourself.

Starting and growing a business is one of the most brutal things you can do, but also one of the most fulfilling ones. And as 2024 approaches, I look forward to continuing the journey of positive impact with @beyond__sapiens which will soon bring me to the 🇦🇪✨. 

Cheers to making 2024 your best year yet, and if you want to 2X your mental performance to achieve your yearly goals by Q2, DM me! 🎯

P.S. Until several years ago, I’d always celebrate New Year’s until late, and I’d always waste Jan. 1st with sleepiness, tiredness, and hangover. Not anymore. So, today, as always, I’ll go to bed at 9 PM to get ready for the 1st sunrise of 2024 at the gym, ready for what 2024 will bring! 🚀✨

Hello,

If you don’t know who I am, allow me to introduce myself. I’m Alex, I’m French but I grew up in Madrid, and I’ve been creating with a camera since 2009. “Professionally” since 2012. 

What gets me out of bed every morning is the deep desire to connect with people and environments. Meeting people and seeing places for the first time is a bit of an addiction.

I make photographs for brands when they hire me. I also make films for them too. I’m known for shooting landscapes and outdoors sports like cycling and hiking. I’ve also built a few companies such as @stayandwander (creative agency) and @wildistco (online photography school). I take pride in sharing what I know about the world of photography and have spent the last five years doing that both online and offline on photography retreats. 

Becoming a photographer happened by accident. As soon as I moved from France to Quebec to finish my design studies I got totally drawn in by the boreal forest and the harsh winters. It was, and still is an endless source of inspiration and peace. 

I struggle with scheduling because I am interested in a lot of things. I also struggle to make the time to go shoot more outside. Also, I’m a pretty bad handyman. 

I know it is very timely to hate on this app and what it is becoming. Although I agree with a lot of it, I’m also immensely thankful for this app that has allowed me to meet thousands of people. Some of which have become friends for life. It has also changed my life by helping create a career path for me and drawing sizeable exposure to my work. That I’ll never forget. 

With that said, It’s up to us to make IG what we want it to be… So here are my commitments to you: 

1. To always tell you like it is
2. To share work I’m proud of
3. To help you if you’re trying to help yourself.. (continued in comments)

Сколько её слёз было пролито и сколько моих нервов потрачено, но надо понимать, что бальные танцы - это парный спорт, и чем раньше станцовываешься с партнёром, тем сильнее пара в будущем.

За это время, что они танцуют вместе, невозможно не заметить их прогресс! Мы очень много занимаемся, и как результат - собираем кубки на каждом турнире, который мы танцуем🏆.

⠀
Иногда Альмира спрашивает, как там Лёня…но теперь я вижу, насколько верным было решение не оставаться в солистках и пережить те слёзы! У девочки проснулся азарт и жажда победы, но важнее всего то, что она получает удовольствие и сияет на турнирах! А то ли ещё будет, вот увидите!

WORKOUT WITH MUM 💙 Every Friday I take mum through a workout in the gym 💪🏼 each week the workout is a little different but today I thought I would show you THIS workout because it is one you can do at 2 different levels ☺️

Some of the exercises we did together, and some I did a more advanced option…so, no matter what level your training partner is, you can get those gains together! 🙌🏼

2 ROUNDS

▪️1. BACK SQUAT
x10

▪️2. ‘W’ ROW
x20

▪️3. SLIDING LUNGES
*or SPLIT SQUATS
x10

▪️4. GORILLA ROW
x10 each side

▪️5. STEP UP
*or HIGH STEP LOWERS
x10

▪️6. SKI ERG
*we aimed for max Cal’s in 1min

▪️7. What we do on our drink breaks 😂

For those of you who haven’t met mum before, she has never really been into fitness or sport her whole life. She grew up in rural Poland and sport and fitness wasn’t really a thing for girls or women. Fast forward to her at 73. I brought her to the gym for a session, she did the whole workout with a smile on her face, no excuses, an open mind, and willingness to try anything (no matter what I throw at her!) 😃 She’s been coming every week, for 3 years. She is my inspiration and I am so proud of her! 🥰

✨ IT’S NEVER TO LATE ✨

HANDSTANDS FOR BEGINNERS 🤸🏽 these can be a tricky (and sometimes scary 😵‍💫) skill to learn…so here are some beginner exercises you can try to help you build:

✅ Confidence upside down
✅ Body awareness when things get flipped upside-down
✅ Good handstand body position
✅ Strength in your shoulders, core & hands

🐌 Start sloooowwww 🐌 
▪️The first time you try, just spend 5minutes having a play. You can do this everyday but have a rest day if you start to feel any pain in your wrists (❗️Remember your wrists & shoulders need to build strength in this new position…this takes time!)
▪️Increase the time you spend on your hands slowly each week. Maybe add a minute or 2 to each session. (Add that rest day when needed!)

✨Key tips✨
▪️Try to build a straight line from your hands to shoulders to hips (in both exercises). A training buddy can help you find this position if you can’t feel it!
▪️Fingertips spread wide & pressing down into the ground
▪️Shoulders squeezing ears & push the ground A W A Y

There are a MILLION more tips that I can share so it’s important to remember handstands are a skill and they are complex! So it’s ok if you don’t get it straight away ☺️ Take it slow and have fun!

Also…I’m super keen to run handstands workshops! First stop will be Perth 📍 Who’s keen?! #hanstandtips #beginnerhandstand #handstand

MOBILITY FOR TIGHT HIPS 💫 These are some of my favourite hip releases 👌🏼 Perfect to do as part of your warm up, before a run, on a recovery day or when you are feeling a bit sore/tired from training… I sometimes get lower back tightness and these also help release tension & pain! ☺️

▪️1. LOW SQUAT
- lower your hips to any position that is manageable and where you can keep your heels on the ground & elbows inside the knees (Level 1,2 & 3 shown in order in the video ☺️)
- if you can reach level 3, aim to pull your belly & chest forward at the bottom, spreading the knees wide.
AREAS RELEASED - Groin, hamstrings, low back

▪️2. LOW LUNGE RAINBOW DIVE
- as you reach back open your chest as much as possible & sink the hips.
- guide the elbow toward the ground reaching as low as you can.
AREAS RELEASED - Groin, hip flexor, glute, hamstring, low back

▪️3. GLUTE SLIDE
- foot rests close to the opposite hand as knee slides through the arms as far as you can.
- for a deeper release, slide the back knee further back into a longer lunge.
AREAS RELEASED - Glutes, hip flexor, hamstrings, low back

How do you think you’ll incorporate these movements into your day? ☺️ let me know! 👇🏼 #hiprelease #hipmobility #hipflexibility #lowbackpain #glutepain #hippain
