The word “lemur” (/ˈliːmər/), from the Latin word “lemures”, means “ghost” or “spirit.” It’s not hard to understand the root of this name when you gaze upon Randrianasolo’s sportive lemur (Lepilemur randrianasoloi), also known as the Bemaraha sportive lemur. They certainly have a spooky gaze. Local legend says that this sportive lemur can cast spells with its intense gaze. I accidentally disturbed this little arboreal night lemur while walking in the daytime (its bedtime) through the dry, deciduous forests within the Tsingy de Bemaraha National Park in western Madagascar. I’m not sure, but it may have placed a curse on me. Fair warning: zooming in MAY cause nightmares. #madagascar #lemur

Unlike most of the world, endemicity is the norm in Madagascar. I eventually learned that I had to stop asking if something I was seeing was endemic because the answer was always “yes”. It became quite comical. The same could be true for whether a species was threatened or not. It was almost always threatened, sadly to say. 

I have always loved chameleons and was excited to see some in the wilds of Madagascar. Here’s another endemic and threatened species, a baby short-horned chameleon (Calumma brevicorne) that I photographed outside of the Andasibe-Mantadia National Park on the eastern side of the island. I like the colors of this photo, along with the precarious perch he/she was hanging on to.  #madagascar #chameleon

How’s it hangin?

A Verreaux's sifaka (Propithecus verreauxi), or the white sifaka (a lemur in the Indriidae family), takes a break from foraging to see where her friends have scurried off to. Rest assured, they are not far. #madagascar #lemur

With pointy white and furry ears, orange eyes (that reflect Berenty’s red soil), a long and beautiful tail, and a seemingly endless desire for play and socialization, the ring-tailed lemur (Lemur catta) is a primate that holds a special place in my heart. I had the pleasure of spending several days photographing them in Madagascar’s Berenty Private Reserve, and I simply could not get enough of their antics. I apologize ahead of time for the lemur photo dump that is sure to follow. 

The most conspicuous feature of the ring-tailed lemur is its long tail that is adorned with 26 black and white alternating rings, the first of which is always white and the last one (the tip of the tail) is always black. The tail is used for balance and communication, not for grabbing (it is not prehensile). 

The ring-tailed #lemur is both endemic to #Madagascar and endangered, facing the loss of their forest habitat as a result of stock overgrazing, field burning/clearing, as well as tree-cutting for making charcoal. National parks and private reserves (such as Berenty) play an important role in the survival of species like these.

Hoy es un día irreal ¡lo logramos!

Hace poco Chris y yo conocimos un programa llamado “causada ciudadanas” liderada por el viceministro @luisernestogl con la cual el pueblo puede organizarse a favor de una causa y pueden hacerse escuchar y generaran un cambio, así que quisimos llevar nuestra voz y el apoyo de nuestra audiencia a otro nivel, desde siempre he querido dejar un legado, algo bueno que trascienda y ayude a la sociedad, hoy con orgullo y mucha nostalgia puedo decir que estamos recogiendo los frutos de una gran lucha que hemos dado 
El 4 de octubre decidimos lanzar una petición en la plataforma “Change.org” llamada “Aquí entran todos” que consiste en crear un sello que pueda vivir en muchos lugares públicos y concurridos, libre de discriminación que apoye la inclusión y la igualdad a pesar de las diferencias de gustos y razas de cada quien, con el fin de acabar poco a poco con la discriminación en nuestro país, naturalizando de una vez por todas esta realidad: la comunidad LGTB existe y ha existido desde tiempos inmemorables y no es una enfermedad, ni un desorden mental
Hoy 1 de marzo vemos el resultado en carne propia, firmaremos el decreto con presidencia y una vez más demostraremos que en redes sociales hay personas que creen en el cambio, que no solo están comentando cosas banales sino que por el contrario encontraron un lugar en donde su voz unida con el resto tiene gran impacto.
Hoy estamos dando un paso gigante en la historia de Colombia (ojalá se inspiren y repliquen esto en otros países) muchos creerían que el pais no estaba preparado para afrontar esta realidad de frente, la comunidad LGBT también son humanos y también tienen derechos como todos, puede sonar mas que obvio, pero es evidente que para muchos necesita ser recordado, hoy Colombia seguirá evolucionando en su proceso de crecer como un país tolerante, hoy yo Juan Pablo Jaramillo y mas de 4,5 millones de personas que pertenecemos a la comunidad LGBT nos sentiremos más seguros, más comprendidos y mejor respaldados que siempre, gracias internet, gracias audiencia querida y gracias gobierno de Colombia por abrir puertas a que estos cambios sucedan. 🐘no olvidare este día🐘 #AquiEntranTodos

[Hong Kong Show] Did you know that diamond crafting company SRK Exports @srk.one houses one of the world’s largest inventories of Twin Diamonds in round and fancy shapes (around 4000 pairs!) ? 

For those unfamiliar with SRK’s Twin diamonds, these stones are cut from the same rough and  have identical parameters, which require meticulous planning and skill to achieve! But how do you achieve this? Let’s find out ⤵️

💎 To get the best shape and maximum weight, the planner has to accurately assume the colour of the final polished diamonds; any mistake in assumption results in a different outcome of the colour.

💎 The cutter has to be mindful of the possibility of generating too much heat during the initial laser-cutting process, which can alter the gem’s hue.

💎 The bruiter during the bruiting stage also takes care to maintain the appropriate thickness of the girdle, as the gem’s hue could change due to a thicker girdle.

💎 The polisher’s keen eyes and understanding of the twins are used to achieve perfectly identical proportions.

📍 If you’d like to discover the magic of Twin Diamonds, visit SRK Exports at the Hong Kong Diamond, Gems & Pearl Show, located in Hall 7, Booth E01 at Asia World Expo until the 2nd of March!

‘В китайской философии есть такое понятие – ‘открывающиеся врата’. Все происходящее, или, как говорится в Книге Перемен, вся тьма вещей, воспринимается как циклы. В каждый текущий момент времени может быть начато и успешно осуществлено не любое произвольное действие или начинание, а только то, которое соответствует характеристикам текущего временного цикла. Если врата открыты, то в них можно войти и задуманное обязательно осуществится, так как ситуация благоприятствует этому. И напротив, если врата закрыты, то начинание обречено на провал. Для реализации замысла следует ждать более подходящего момента. Время – сущность ощутимая и с ним можно взаимодействовать. Если научиться ощущать его, то оно начинает и работать в тебе по-другому’. 

Это трактовка своевременности, ключевого понятия, китайской философии, от @bvinogrodskiy Мы только можем стараться на этом пути, балансировать между двумя понятиями - своевременности и чувства меры. Мера тоже связана со временем. Вот этих двух качеств я желаю себе и вам, любимые, в этом году, с такими мыслями я вхожу в Новый год уже по китайской традиции. Встретили его в теплом кругу друзей ❤️

Jump through, straight legs sit down. This is a phrase that you will hear over and over again and every single Ashtanga Yoga class. If you keep practicing, you may even hear this phrase in your dreams.

Learning to jump through holds so much information about inversions, strength, mental, focus, and surrender. You can’t rush the process of building the foundational strength in order to learn the lesson of jumping through. You can, however, focus on the step-by-step technique that will eventually lead you there. 

I remember when I first started practicing how frustrating it was that I couldn’t do this movement. Now, more than 20 years later, I still think there are many ways to refine the movement and get stronger. What’s important to me is not the performative aspect, but the connection of breath, awareness and mental focus. This is the essence of the flow that happens when our mind and body are completely harmonized.

Now I’m missing hearing my teacher tell us all to jump through as I unroll my mat on my own. 

Keep practicing 🙏

We bear the fruits of every action we take. Karma is a universal law of action. Both the intended and unintended consequences of our actions rest on our shoulders. I don’t see this a zero sum game of winners and losers or some harsh deity that issues judgement. Instead, every experience is all about learning, growing and evolving. 

An action we take with the best intentions reverberates for lifetimes with both positive and negative impact on our lives and the lives of those around us. We can be working through the residual impact for as long as need in order to integrate the spiritual lesson. Repetition isn’t always due to failure. Sometimes it’s about seeing another person or reaching a deeper layer. 

Once we are strong enough to see ourselves clearly, we are ready to really go through the process of spiritual awakening. Everything we do in three practice prepares us for increasingly deeper levels of self-realization. We can’t rush. We can only go at our own pace and trust that what is meant to happen will happen when it’s meant to happen. 

Keep practicing 🙏

As I departed LAX to fly to Québec this week, there was a moment where I had the most profound sense of gratefulness for the fact that I can live in California. A state that is home to this spot off Highway 1, one of the most beautiful scenic drives in the United States. One of my favorite drives anywhere in the world in fact, even though I’ve been to more than 50 countries. The longer @dante.vincent & I live in California, the more grateful I find myself becoming.

Yesterday, Chris Burkard shared a post where he said, “It feels like the more we talk the less the words mean. I, for one, look forward to the silence the outdoors can bring...”

I‘m pretty sure he wasn’t talking about the Highway when he wrote that caption but I instantly thought of it. It’s the driving equivalent of a hike into back country. There’s so little development along large portions of the drive, save the road itself, that you can forget the stress of life in a city and feel so much closer to nature without needing the kind of outdoor experience that I think prohibits a lot of people from being out in nature more. Or even just caring about the planet period.

The noise of the car itself fades away on a drive like this and you hear instead the sound of waves, of birds, of the wind that you can’t see but you sure can feel. Even the sunshine feels like it has a quiet melody. It’s drives like this that helped me think about the planet as a place I wanted to save, not just experience. I’ll never forget the first time I saw this scene before there was Instagram and before I even began working in travel.

🇭🇷 After Chioggia and Koper, we sailed to Zadar during our hosted itinerary with @vikingcruises last month. 

From there we drove inland for a day trip @dante.vincent had chosen because it included a bird sanctuary and rehabilitation center with the possibility to try our hand at falconry. That didn’t end up happening. 

But we still got to see birds, we heard a very entertaining lecture, and we were able to spend time in Krka National Park. 

I was surprised by how green it still was for October, and the fact they have multiple blooming periods each year for the small purple cyclamen that can carpet the ground in parts of the park! If it’s your first time ever in Croatia, I’d recommend opting for the included walking tour of the Old Town of Zadar. It’s so charming and was one of my favorite stops during my last visit to Croatia many years ago now.

Do you recognize this island?

It’s probably the most recognizable Slovenian landmark and yet from my friends who love the country, I know it’s far from the only thing to enjoy in 🇸🇮 

Still with my one afternoon ashore in the country as part of our hosted @vikingcruises, I wanted to visit understand why it’s so famous! 🤔

It was a 2 hour bus ride from the port of Koper and after arriving we took traditional Pletna boats to the island in the alpine lake that doesn’t allow motored craft and was once home to a temple to Ziva [the Slavic goddess of love and fertility] ❤️

I fell hard for these gleaming wooden boats with awnings that are compared to Venetian gondolas, passed down through the families that captain them. They’re controlled using two long wooden poles and to do so is to be called a Pletnarstvo.

On the island: visit the Church of  the Assumption whose current Baroque design dates to the 17th century with a chapel from the year 1004. Ring the bell from the 1500s to make your wish come true. Then climb the tower for views across the tiled roof to Bled Castle.

Before departing, get gelato at Café Potičnica. You’ll earn it once you’ve climbed the 99 steps from the boat launch and walked all the way up the 52-meter high tower!

So what makes it all so special that it’s one of the most photographed spots in the world? I still don’t know. 😂 But it is a charming area! 🥰 And the lake is so beautiful when the sun is shining and that alpine water gleams turquoise and green. Plus the excursion did make me want to return to see much more of Slovenia! If you’ve been, where else do you think people should visit in the country?

#MyVikingStory #VikingCruises

Our ship was due to leave port in a few hours and I felt the urgency of the sun’s journey as it fell further and further toward the horizon visible between the masts of sailboats in the harbor. ⛵️ I could relax, unpack, and unwind. But I’d never seen Chioggia. 🇮🇹 What was it like? I had to know! And so I made my way down, out, away, with the wind in my hair and a pep in my step. 🏃‍♀️ Between tall buildings, through narrow alleys, under colorful laundry and past the eyes of a nonna or two I made my way to the busiest street in town: Corso del Popolo. It was buzzing with a post-work energy and a golden hour glow. ☀️ Residents on bicycles sped past me as I meandered under colonnades and by shops to observe a group of mothers circled around strollers chatting away while their older children played in the square, a couple alone at a café, and men debating over cold glasses of birra. 🍻 Further wanderlust drove me on to see if I could find a quiet spot and I discovered vibrant reflections making a type of modern art painting on the calm canal water; before raising my head to observe the alley before me overflowing with rainbows. 🌈 A promise of things to come? 🤔🤞🤞

Made it to Venice, Italy yesterday with only enough time to see sunset and then find a place to eat dinner. But it didn’t really matter because any amount of time in Venezia always thrills me to my core. And what a sunset we saw!! 😍

I am sad to report that crowd level seems to be back to pre-pandemic levels and for myself I think this will be my last time here unless it’s in the dead of winter when there are likely to be less tourists (?) as being part of over-tourism for a place nearly being loved to death, doesn’t feel really good. I need to do more research and talk to more people that live here before I make any final decisions. 

What are your thoughts on over-tourism or visiting Venice? 

The city is seeking to combat over-tourism with a tax for day trippers and other tourists that I’ve outlined on my blog. I personally think it’s a good move. And I will be curious to see what residents like my friend @neumarc think as it gets implemented and we see whether or not it has a positive impact. 

Venice also banned large cruise ships from the Venetian Lagoon as it caused intense damage to the ecosystem when they were allowed. Speaking of cruises, I’m in Italy to head to the port and fishing town of Chiaggio where we are joining @vikingcruises for their “Empires of the Mediterranean” sailing. It is Dante’s first time on a cruise and Viking is one of the only lines I will go on an ocean cruise with because their ship has a passenger capacity less then 1/3 the size of the average for the industry. They also seem to be making honest strides to ensure they operate in ways that are as responsible and ethical as possible. I’ve also never met an employee who didn’t LOVE working for Viking. The ones I’ve met when on the river and one ocean cruise so far have been some of the happiest tourism employees I’ve found the world over.

This is starting to sound like a commercial 😂 and I didn’t mean to do that. But I am grateful to be hosted by Viking again so I can share more about them. AMA in the comments and I’ll answer honestly ⤵️

Thank you for making it this far. I hope your week is off to a great start ❤️

#myvikingstory #myvikingjourney #vikingcruises

I met @jennifer_clasen at Sony Kando and after we both got back to the city, we got together at one of our mutually favorite places in LA. Following my introduction to Venezuelan arepas at @amarachocolate, her idea and a very good one!, we spent all day in the @thehuntingtonlibrary gardens deep in discussion about life and in frequent meditation over the smallest details. I learned more about her incredible work as a set photographer for film and TV, please check out her work at the link in her profile. Occasionally we paused to do nothing more than watch koi pass in and out of the colorful reflections on otherwise still bodies of water; both marveling at finding someone else we could do that with who didn’t feel it was wasted time. It was such a treat to deepen the friendship that began in Utah. 

I can’t put into words how grateful I am to the Sony family of brands for hosting me in a place where I could learn about their Create Action initiative; and that brought together so many phenomenal people like Jen, Brooke, Autumn, Nancy, Endia, Stormy, Kayla, Amber, Michelle, Monica, Michaela, Sapna, Juan, [and more!] who made me feel so welcome but also so seen. I hope my first Kando wasn’t my last. But no matter what happens, I’ve got a garden of memories that I couldn’t be more thankful for. 

I’ll return to them over and over as I endeavor to earn a more permanent place amongst the amazing souls that are Sony Artisans, Ambassadors, and Alpha Collective members. It can feel like not that often that global corporations really get things right for their customers and advocates. But Sony seems to have found the magic so many seek. And that’s why I’m glad I made the choice to shoot with their gear starting in 2017 and why I will continue to do so. #SonyAlpha #SonyAlphaFemale

My favourite place in Iran: „The Lut Desert, widely referred to as Dasht-e Lut (Persian: دشت لوت, "Emptiness Plain"), is a large salt desert located in the provinces of Kerman and Sistan and Baluchestan, Iran. It is the world's 33rd-largest desert, and was included on UNESCO's World Heritage List on July 17, 2016. The name is derived from 'Lut' which means bare and empty in Persian and 'dasht' which means plain in Persian. The surface of its sand has been measured at temperatures as high as 70.7 °C (159.3 °F),making it one of the world's driest and hottest places.“ - Wikipedia

People often asking about my true passion for my work . It’s easy to explain. the answer is quite straightforward. Many barbers and hairdressers resonate with this sentiment. The ability to influence someone’s appearance and enhance their self-esteem is what fuels my love for my profession. It’s powerful to make someone look different and happy 😊 

I saw a documentary about the YAKUZA gang from Japan. I was fascinated by their appearance. This intrigue led me to seek to recreate a similar style with my unique twist. but I couldn’t find the right person with tattoos and piercings. So, I had an idea: I could create the look from scratch. I found David, a sophisticated and classy individual with a captivating personality. even though he doesn’t have tattoos or piercings. I bought some fake tattoos and piercings online and used them to change his look a lot. I wanted him to look like a gang member who was interviewed by fashion magazine. I kept some of his natural style and added a tougher, more masculine touch.

Thoughts 💭 ?

Cyprus: Where history, culture, and natural beauty converge to create unforgettable experiences.

•Explore the medieval harbour and fortress of Kyrenia Castle, offering panoramic views of the coast.

•Explore the picturesque village of Karmi, known for its traditional architecture and stunning views of the Mediterranean.

•Wander through the charming streets of Famagusta’s Old Town, filled with history and culture.

•Admire the historic architecture of Bellapais Abbey, nestled in the tranquil village of Bellapais.

•Petra tou Limniti: Where rugged cliffs meet the endless blue, a hidden gem along Cyprus’s coast awaits your discovery.

•Discover the ancient city of Salamis, with its well-preserved ruins and stunning seaside location.

In 2007 I was hired by @timberland to do a series of ads where they wanted a sense of motion conveyed, without using motion blur. I pitched them on using light streaks to show motion paths, by strapping headlamps to hands and wrists of athletes. This one here was with my friend @joekinder climbing on a bridge near Manitou Springs, CO. To capture this frame we determined the end point of the frame where my flash would fire and freeze the action, which is essentially what frame 3 is. Joe started at the base, and climbed to that point with headlamps on wrists and feet, while I left the shutter open, firing the flash once he hit our established end point. The total exposure time was 94 seconds, leaving behind his light path in a fun way, all done entirely in camera.

It’s been a long time since I’ve introduced myself on Instagram. I don’t think I ever did. One day, 12 years ago, I was here, and that was that. But I’ve recently committed to going back to basics in my life and thought that was worth further explanation here.

In my time on Instagram, I’ve been a chef turned professional Instagrammer and travel photographer. I’ve become a consultant, campaign manager and public speaker. I’ve created an online photography course, co-founded an event and run photography tours to Zimbabwe. I’ve been to all seven continents with paid work, and during Covid, I became a business coach and the Managing Director of a seven-figure startup. Then I gave it all away.

As my successes piled up, I realised that not only did I now know who I was without them, I didn’t believe that I was enough without them either.

2022 became the year of undoing. I undid my business, stopped chasing the money and adulation, stopped creating and gave myself space to figure out who I am underneath it all. Not only did I find out, but I learned to love myself without any of it.

As I continue to sit into my power, embrace motherhood and find joy in the everyday, I also feel a calling to share my journey. You can read my blogs, subscribe to my emails and turn on post notifications for my Instagram stories if you want to come along.

My name is Lauren. I’m a storyteller.

This is one of the most confronting images that I took in Borneo and, for me, this was one of the hardest things I’ve ever had to shoot. Afterwards I went back to my room and just cried and cried and I still cry to think about it now. I’ve seen pictures like this in the media and spared them a few minutes of sympathy before moving on with my life, but seeing this with my own eyes affected me fundamentally. These are the long term cages, for animals that have slipped through the cracks. They’ve either been too big to handle or sick with contagious diseases that can’t enter the main population. Some are just waiting until the resources are there to put them onto a pre release island, some can’t get along with other orangutans, some have been broken by humans and some are in long term sanctuary and will never have freedom again. Small though these cages are they can cost up to $20,000 and the resources aren’t there to replace them with better facilities, yet. Although I saw many happy endings for orangutans in Samboja and Nyaru Menteng, I also saw too many animals in these cages. Depressed and dejected, although some are angry still and rattle their cages and spit as you walk by. It’s the difficult job of the program director here to prioritize cases, move animals around the different facilities and decide which are eligible for release. With so many moving parts they’re doing a fine job with the resources they have. Please leave a like and comment, even if you don’t ‘like’ the situation. The more awareness we can spread the better. There’s more information in my Instagram story, with video too. Oh, and this is Roslyn. 💔@bosfoundation #orangutanfreedom #saveorangutans

It’s so interesting to pay attention to the cycles. For me, that’s been my newly returned menstrual cycle, but before that, I was paying particular attention to the lunar cycles and earth cycles (seasons).

I notice how much I struggle to honour low-energy days. I want to DO things. I get into all kinds of “stories” about what it means about me if I’m not productive.

High-energy days are a lot easier. For me, MY personality. But guess what? When I honour the low-energy days and get through on the bare minimum, the high-energy days are amplified big time!

I had some much slower days last week from Wednesday - Saturday, allowing myself to rest, reflect and turn inwards. From Sunday onwards, WHOA! Energy to BURN!

I’m really looking forward to experimenting more with this in 2024. It’s also a wonderful practice to get more into your body and be more present. Paying attention and being aware is the first step to change.

#cycles #lunarcycle #menstrualcycle #spinningwheels #motivation #energy #intuition #embodiment

Whoa. What a weekend! This weekend, I had not one but two kids' birthday parties to attend. Don’t get me wrong, I LOVE them. The party food, the cake, the nostalgia and, of course, the excitement on my kid's faces. Kids parties are great.

They’re also very, very, very stimulating! And this weekend, I made the rookie error of putting off my journaling and beach visit until afterwards, meaning I was going into each party with my cup empty.

By yesterday afternoon, I was in struggle town. I was in a functional freeze state - disassociating and reaching for the phone for some mindless scrolling. I was highly emotional, very overwhelmed and still highly stimulated. I recognised the state and needed to make decisions to allow me to process and regulate.

I struggled to fall asleep after it all, physically feeling my body twitch as I came down. It’s a funny thing to know your own limits and still push past them because you don’t want to miss out. The good news is that I’m learning. It’s time to honour my capacity more.

Today, I wanted to ease back into work with some slow and creative tasks, including editing a small gallery of shots from a women’s circle I attended two weeks ago.

It’s not an easy thing for me to admit that I’m not superwoman, for me to know and honour my limits. Although I CAN do a lot, I don’t want to do a lot if it doesn’t feel good.

Yesterday afternoon, I didn’t feel good. This afternoon, I felt very good. I allow the feeling to guide me. ❤️

#womenscircle #followthefeeling #emotionalregulation #nervoussystemregulation #fomo #surrender #superwoman #honourmyself

I had an interesting day yesterday. I was feeling low on energy and low on motivation. It was probably due to the New Moon, a time for introspection and letting go rather than hustling and DOING.

Naturally, I didn’t feel like doing a thing and cancelled all the tasks I’d planned to work on in favour of doing some creative stuff at a snail's pace.

Even though I’d acknowledged the energy AND consciously chose to work with my (lower) energy, I still found myself getting into stories about it.

“It’s only week one of being back at work, and you’re already making excuses; this is why you’re not going to make it.”

“You’re feeling guilty for not doing much, and guilt is a low-vibration emotion. You know this, and yet you haven’t even mastered shifting emotions.”

“You can’t even get anything done. How will you do everything you want to do this year?”

Blah, blah, blah.

But I kept choosing to sit with the discomfort and my inner knowing that we are simply not designed to hustle every single day. We are cyclical beings, and we work best when we allow for that.

This morning, I woke up, and all I wanted to do was create. I started writing like crazy, had an idea for a book and even took my camera down to the beach. This isn’t the best shot, just the only shot I was able to edit briefly while I was watching the kids. I felt great!

It’s important to remember on the bad days that the good days are always coming. It will be my practice this year to sink more deeply into my downtime and continue to trust that I will get everything I want. I feel that so hard.

#photography #creativelife #creativeliving #newmoon #newmoonenergy #cyclical #surrender #trusttheuniverse

I’ve spent the last 18 months finding myself amongst the chaos of motherhood, exiting a business I loved and dismantling a set of beliefs that no longer served me.

During that time the biggest gift I gave myself was the gift of space. Space to reflect. Space to be curious about my life. Space to create without pressure. It was quite possibly the most impactful period of my life.

Amongst the many things I learned about myself, and life, is how to pay attention to the cycles. Because I’m not menstruating (still breastfeeding), I am more strongly impacted by the lunar cycle. My energy, emotions and moments of inspiration are all loosely following the cycles of the moon.

At first I didn’t notice at all. Then it all seemed coincidental. But today, noticing that it is the new moon and feeling into my body and energy, I feel deeply aligned with it.

The New Moon is a time for reflection and planting seeds for the next cycle. It is not a time to be kicking goals. And I feel that HARD in my body.

To honour how I feel, and the cycles, I’m adjusting my day today to create more space and execute easier tasks. I can smash out the bulk work when my energy starts to build again.

If you’re interested to know more about the cycles, I’ve been using @janehardwickecollings app ‘Spinning Wheels’ and the @magic_of_i .

I know how woo woo this sounds. And I know we live in a society that doesn’t let us believe we have the space to choose. But we do. Life has so much more meaning when we slow down, honour ourselves and trust that it will all get done.

#trust #theuniverse #newmoon #introspection #spinningwheels #thecycles #surrender2024

Last year I set a modest goal for myself to move my body two times a week.

One of those times was a half hour personal training session at my local private gym, a cost that I definitely could not afford at the time.

But health was high on my list of priorities and I partnered up with a friend to go halves in a 2-on-1 half hour session once a week. It’s not much. Half an hour.

But I’ll share something with you. That half an hour session, executed just 15 times, has been the catalyst for my new fitness goals for 2024.

Today was my last day doing personal training. For now at least. I’m joining a gym.

I sat on this decision for a long time because I have so little time to work, and I really didn’t want my fitness to interfere with my work time. I am also still struggling with motivation, which was the reason why I needed a personal trainer in the first place.

Then, in an instant brainwave, I realised that I could find a gym with a crèche that runs group fitness classes and train in my parenting hours. (Dreamboat and I equally split parenting hours and working hours.)

I’ve tested it out and my kids LOVED the crèche! And I loved getting back on a spin bike again. I was grinning from ear to ear.

The point of my story is twofold. One is that you don’t need to go from zero to a hundred. A year of gently adapting to exercise again created the momentum to set bigger goals this year. I’ve got my whole life to get my fitness on track. This year I hope to move my body four times a week, upping the ante on the intensity.

The second lesson is this, no matter what your personal circumstances are, there is a solution to your challenges. I have two babies and a business to restart in less than 25 hours a week. I also have zero motivation to exercise of my own accord. But I sat into the problem and found the solution. There is ALWAYS a solution.

Wish me luck on my fitness journey. ❤️

P.S. The beach was almost like this today! I’m thinking of taking my underwater housing out soon. 😱

Everywhere I look, I see people I love and admire talking about their yearly planning and sharing their processes.

I love planning. During the Phhnix days, I was a staunch defender of planning and saw first-hand how planning creates the structure to achieve any goal. It’s an infallible system.

I also find planning to be personally suffocating. I don’t know if it’s remnants of the business PTSD I have (joking, but also not), some other type of block or internal resistance, or if my intuition is telling me not to plan. Hear me out.

At the end of the day, the point of a plan is to achieve goals. A plan is a tool. Me? I’ve never had an issue executing tasks or achieving goals. On the contrary, my problem in business is usually taking on too much and spending my days in overwhelm.

I’m tired of trying to do things the way that other people do them. 2024 is a year for me to get really fucking curious about my working style and test out new ways. Ways that might or might not work, but will teach me at the very least.

So I won’t be planning this year, at least not beyond the simple note listing my goals and a running to-do list. Instead, I’ll be spending the majority of my working hours taking care of myself so that the work can flow like magic.

This looks like meditation, gym, beach and personal development during work time, and brief periods of intense focus to get through the actual work.

I’ll be sure to let you know how it works out for me. I’m a multi-dimensional being attempting to undo every story I’ve ever been told about success. If I can’t FEEL good and be in my body, then I don’t want it. No amount of success is worth my peace.

Portraits from afar. ✨
An rather unusual set of photos on this account, but somehow Oman inspired me to shoot more local culture and people. I don’t like being a camera-in-peoples-faces-tourist, so here’s a set of portraits from a far. A couple notes about each of these shots:

1. 📍Fort Nizwa - I liked how the soft light matched the rounded shapes of this historical landmark.

2. 📍Wahiba Sands - I was snapping portraits of a camel when suddenly a truck with smiling Omani passed by. Big fan of the camel’s lip.

3. 📍Nizwa - Blue hour, neon lights and a lonely chair. I really enjoyed this scene, especially as two men walked by.

4. 📍Sur harbour - I was snapping photos on a mountain by the bay when this heroic fisherman cruised through the scene.

5. 📍Bidiyah - It was midday, but the smoke from burnt palm leaves created a soft atmosphere among the palm trees. 

6. 📍Somewhere in between - I loved the old Toyota trucks I saw all over Oman. Fun fact: the boy drove off by himself moments later.

7. 📍Nizwa - Two strangers walking down jewellery lane. I really liked the look of the large arabic signs on every business. 

8. 📍Sur beach - Loved watching all the different activities on the beach. Men landing boats, Women picknicking by the car, kids playing in the water, dogs, birds, everything.

9. 📍Sultan Qaboos Grand Mosque - A family chilling on the steps of one of the worlds largest mosques. If felt truly peaceful.

This might be the longest caption ever, but I thought some people might enjoy the extra insights. Did you? 🤚

Ophelia

Lucinda Harmon Jackman,
4th wife of 7 to my namesake Levi Jackman, began her crossing of the American Great Plains on this day in 1849 in search of a new life free from persecution from the US government and religious zealots who declared her lifestyle as a Mormon an affront to god and society. Though historical accounts of Lucinda, my 3x Great Grandmother, are difficult to find in comparison to the documents detailing the life of her husband, the stirring personal parallels in our lives make it easy to imagine her as familiar. Because of her beliefs and non-traditional marriage, before trekking across the continent she was a societal outcast. She left the only world she’d ever known behind for a new chosen community, with whom she faced probable death in hopes of building a space where the next generation of their kind could feel safe. My heart finds a queerness in her story.
I don’t know if the Lucinda of 1849 would be able to comprehend my queer existence today, but that doesn’t diminish my desire to walk where she walked, reach through time and thank her for her precedent of pursuing love despite the sacrifices it would demand of her.

Thank you to @chloembower and @sammydigi for assisting on this project.

Image theft and copyright infringements have long since become an everyday annoyance for me as a photographer. On all continents and at all levels of education, mayors, theatre directors, architects, professors, students, art directors or gallery owners etc. use my pictures without authorization, proper credits, any payments and steal my work. Here is another inglorious example:
.
2 images from my awarded series „The Red Wall“ were used by one of the oldest Spanish newspaper »Las Provincias« @lasprovincias for an article about Bofill’s »La Muralla Roja«. @bofillarquitectura 
.
My photographs were used:
.
- without authorization by me as the photographer
- without credits and mention of me as the photographer
- without paying me as the photographer
.
The people at “Las Provincias” rejected my offer to subsequently purchase a usage license. The file names of the two images even contain my name! The photo editor @txemarodriguez is apparently too lazy to even cover up the fact that the images are being used illegally. The Wallpaper Magazine* paid to publish my images, why aren’t you paying?
.

Я обычно в аэропорту улыбаюсь над теми, кто путешествует с тысячей чемоданов, а теперь сами впервые повезем чемоданы, сложенные горой на тележке 🤣🤣🤣
Ну и по такому случаю я решила чемоданы обновить)) снова не стала изменять себе и взяла @mysamsonite 💗 теперь у меня крутой комплект из одной линейки🥰
Перед отъездом шопинг вышел на новый уровень)) знаю, что еще приедем, но зачем отказывать себе в удовольствии в эти суетные дни переезда?🤣💰

Давненько не рассказывала вам о фаворитах косметики)) а это не значит, что я ею не пользуюсь! Просто то дела, то поездки, то скорая с мигалками, то рутина, то вот переезд, как сейчас 🙈 
На лето обожаю легкие тона - на более прохладную погоду увлажняющий флюид от @makeupforeverrussia, он делает лицо красивым, но не видно, что вы накрашены. На жару @diormakeup #backstage, он тоже невидимый, но при этом выдерживает жару и делает очень красивую кожу.
Уход у меня сейчас от @biotherm, супер легкий и воздушный, под ним кожа дышит, гели и кремы моментально впитываются, достаточно увлажняют, но ничего не плывет на них летом. 
Когда вечером хочу побаловать кожу, то наношу plumping маску от @clarinsrussia💗 не знаю, чего я сразу не стала ею пользоваться и больше использовала увлажняющую. Эта обалденно моментально оживляет лицо! Кожа более упругая, напитанная и свежая. Если хотите бодрости, берите ее, а если просто увлажнения, то можно голубую.
В жару и сезон цветения на глазах моих держатся только два средства - тушь @maybelline_ru #lashsensational и карандаш @marcjacobsbeauty 💗 с весны кроме них почти ничего не использую. На брови карандаш @zoevacosmetics arsenic, сверху прозрачный гель @urbandecayrussia - идеальное комбо! Гель этот обожаю, отлично держит и не делает комков лишних, а карандаш идеален по цвету и мягкости нанесения.
Для контуринга бессменный kevin aucoin. Вот хайлайтер этот от @bobbibrownrussia очень люблю за цвет, но таки пришлось отказаться от него, забивает поры и делает какие-то твердые подкожники, которые оооочень долго проходят и никак не поддаются никаких воздействиям 😭😭😭
На губы обожаю сейчас использовать сливовую глянцевую помаду от @clarinsrussia ☀️
Что из этого пробовали? Совпали впечатления?

My Rainbow Baby journey 😢🌈

Many people don’t know that Tyson is a rainbow baby🌈👶🏽. For those that don’t know what that means, it’s that Tyson came after us miscarrying our baby before him. It’s taken a few years to decide if we wanted to share this, and just as long to feel comfortable taking about it. 

After hearing of struggles to get pregnant and miscarriages from people around us, we felt that we wanted to share so that others going through this feel less alone, as well as to give some hope. 

In early 2017, my husband and I got the wonderful news that we were going to have a baby, we were ecstatic and began planning for this blessed baby's arrival. I chatted with the baby regularly, and planned its nursery, planned our announcement etc. 

Then suddenly, just past 12 weeks, we lost our beloved baby. The pain, sadness and loneliness that goes along with this was unimaginable. I’m not sure why there is so much secrecy around a miscarriage here in North America, it’s makes it so much worse. 

Not everything was ‘evacuated’ when it happened so I was still carrying the baby after the miscarriage. When I asked my doctor what to do, she said I had to wait for it to pass naturally (which isn’t true for everyone) 😞

For 9 months I still had all the hormones and the baby which made it so much harder to get past what happened. When I eventually found a new doctor, she took care of me and helped us to complete this chapter. We were finally able to mourn & have closure. When we were ready, we tried again 😀

We are thankful that all the stars aligned to bring us the most special gift of our life, and the following year we got the news that we were pregnant again and Tyson was on his way. The main reason to share this story is to give hope to those out there going though some of the challenges of this. We send love to our little angel in heaven, and thanks for our little Tyson. 

 Sending hope, love & baby dust to anyone in need… hugs xoxo ❤️🙏🏼🌈

#normalizemiscarriage  #rainbowbaby #miscarriages

Don’t let the scale dictate your journey! 🚫 

Weight can fluctuate for various reasons like water retention (think salty meals, workouts, or hormones) and other factors beyond fat gain. ⁣Remember, it’s just one piece of the puzzle!⁣
⁣
The scale provides data, but a sudden increase doesn’t mean you’ve gained fat. 

Trust the process!  For instance, after a heavy workout, your body might retain water to aid muscle repair, causing a temporary increase.⁣
⁣
Focus on progress beyond the numbers—because you’re more than a digit!  Celebrate victories that go beyond the scale. 🎉 

Notice how your clothes fit better, feel the increased energy levels, revel in improved sleep quality, and relish in the compliments you receive.⁣

Keep pushing, stay positive, and remember: You’re on the path to becoming your best self! 👊🏼😘

Are you have trouble drinking enough water everyday?? 💦 

I can help!! 👊🏼❤️

I want to show you one of my favorite hacks for getting my daily water in! Now ideally you wanna aim to get in 2 to 3 liters of water in per day. I know!

 That’s a loooottta of water! And if you are not used to drinking so much water, there is definitely a learning curve! Below you will find my tip for staying hydrated and a trick on how to make water taste yummy!

Infused watermelon and basil  water 🍉 🌿   

The flavor is a water melony with a hint of basil, but, the scent of the basil as you drink it is intoxicating. Scrunch the basil in your hands before adding to the water to increase the flavor. Give it at least 2 hours in the fridge to soak up the flavor.

I like to let all infused water sit at least 2 hours but not more than two days before drinking.  You can make little waters like this or make one big jug to finish that day. Try to use organic produce and wash everything thoroughly.
